1
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,135
Finally.

2
00:00:58,135 --> 00:00:59,303
This is now...

3
00:00:59,970 --> 00:01:00,971
The real deal.

4
00:01:00,971 --> 00:01:02,139
(Last, Moon Se Hoon)

5
00:01:02,139 --> 00:01:03,507
Everything comes down to Se Hoon's choice.

6
00:01:07,811 --> 00:01:10,981
(Jin Joo has 0 votes right now.)

7
00:01:10,981 --> 00:01:13,183
Jin Joo is the only one left alone.

8
00:01:13,183 --> 00:01:16,019
So choosing Jin Joo...

9
00:01:16,019 --> 00:01:18,755
- I don't think that'd be a bad choice.
- I agree, it wouldn't be bad.

10
00:01:22,092 --> 00:01:25,796
(Who will Moon Se Hoon choose?)

11
00:01:27,531 --> 00:01:29,900
(Turn)

12
00:01:32,069 --> 00:01:34,738
Right up until the moment I stepped out,

13
00:01:34,738 --> 00:01:36,873
I was really torn about who to choose.

14
00:01:36,873 --> 00:01:38,642
Either Myo Jin or Tae In.

15
00:01:38,642 --> 00:01:41,078
I knew Seung Hak would be next to Myo Jin,

16
00:01:41,578 --> 00:01:44,548
and Hyun Jun would be next to Tae In.

17
00:01:48,318 --> 00:01:49,653
That kept bothering me.

18
00:01:49,653 --> 00:01:52,422
Deep down,
I kind of hoped he'd come to me.

19
00:01:56,026 --> 00:01:59,663
(After much thought,
Se Hoon finally steps forward.)

20
00:02:11,174 --> 00:02:12,976
Where? He went to Myo Jin.

21
00:02:12,976 --> 00:02:14,511
- Who?
- To Myo Jin.

22
00:02:14,511 --> 00:02:15,445
There?

23
00:02:15,445 --> 00:02:16,947
(Moon Se Hoon chooses Kim Myo Jin.)

24
00:02:18,849 --> 00:02:19,683
Did you sleep well?

25
00:02:27,791 --> 00:02:30,794
The person I chose was Myo Jin.

26
00:02:31,762 --> 00:02:33,463
In the middle of
that emotional whirlwind...

27
00:02:33,997 --> 00:02:37,134
between Tae In and Hyun Jun,

28
00:02:37,434 --> 00:02:40,771
I think we three were
having a really hard time.

29
00:02:40,771 --> 00:02:47,344
And since Myo Jin
is also someone I'm interested in,

30
00:02:47,544 --> 00:02:50,013
I felt it was a very natural choice.

31
00:02:50,013 --> 00:02:51,682
But Seung Hak is there too.

32
00:02:52,416 --> 00:02:53,784
What about Seung Hak?

33
00:02:53,784 --> 00:02:55,319
Why isn't he mentioning Seung Hak?

34
00:02:55,319 --> 00:02:58,522
Why is it not okay to go to them,

35
00:02:58,522 --> 00:02:59,623
but okay to go there?

36
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:03,593
- So what happens to our cutie Seung Hak?
- What kind of situation is this?

37
00:03:05,662 --> 00:03:11,568
(All the men have made their choices.)

38
00:03:13,270 --> 00:03:14,938
(Men's choice date
Kim Jin Joo, 0 votes)

39
00:03:14,938 --> 00:03:16,506
Jin Joo.

40
00:03:16,506 --> 00:03:20,210
For two days in a row,
Jin Joo has received zero votes.

41
00:03:20,210 --> 00:03:22,346
She must be feeling absolutely terrible.

42
00:03:24,147 --> 00:03:29,753
(Min Cheol chooses Hyun Jin
instead of Jin Joo.)

43
00:03:30,988 --> 00:03:31,855
(Myo Jin's team heads out
in Se Hoon's car.)

44
00:03:31,855 --> 00:03:34,391
- I'll be your driver, boss.
- Thank you.

45
00:03:34,391 --> 00:03:36,426
Sorry for interrupting your date,
Seung Hak.

46
00:03:36,426 --> 00:03:37,327
No, it's fine.

47
00:03:38,295 --> 00:03:39,496
Seung Hak, do you have any lip balm?

48
00:03:40,464 --> 00:03:42,299
I don't it with me now.

49
00:03:42,799 --> 00:03:44,468
Do you want some lip tint?

50
00:03:44,468 --> 00:03:45,602
For real.

51
00:03:45,602 --> 00:03:46,603
Lip tint?

52
00:03:47,037 --> 00:03:48,639
I haven't heard about lip tint in forever.

53
00:03:49,139 --> 00:03:51,942
But you might end up looking
like a man wearing makeup like a woman.

54
00:03:51,942 --> 00:03:53,010
(Up close)

55
00:03:53,010 --> 00:03:54,678
This hurts my heart so much.

56
00:03:54,678 --> 00:03:57,347
Our cutie Seung Hak
is sitting right behind them.

57
00:03:57,347 --> 00:03:59,216
I really hate that.

58
00:03:59,216 --> 00:04:02,286
(A scene too painful to watch)

59
00:04:02,286 --> 00:04:04,087
Right in front of him...

60
00:04:04,087 --> 00:04:06,523
This isn't like bringing a nephew
along your date or something.

61
00:04:06,523 --> 00:04:07,891
What is this situation?

62
00:04:07,891 --> 00:04:08,892
Exactly.

63
00:04:13,063 --> 00:04:16,733
You do look cuter with your hair down.

64
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:19,236
My heart hurts so much.

65
00:04:19,236 --> 00:04:21,104
If you push your bangs back,

66
00:04:21,104 --> 00:04:24,775
you have an intense look,
so it's kind of hard to approach.

67
00:04:25,375 --> 00:04:26,677
But with them down,
I seem easier to act rude to.

68
00:04:26,677 --> 00:04:27,978
Yeah, kind of.

69
00:04:27,978 --> 00:04:29,780
Not exactly "easy to act rude to."

70
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:31,081
But it feels like it'd be easier
to relax around you

71
00:04:32,416 --> 00:04:34,151
But somehow...

72
00:04:34,151 --> 00:04:36,186
seeing Seung Hak sitting back there...

73
00:04:36,186 --> 00:04:38,789
feels like I'm looking at myself.

74
00:04:39,890 --> 00:04:41,158
The guy sitting in the front
is Kim Yo Han.

75
00:04:42,526 --> 00:04:45,395
The one in the front is Kim Yo Han,

76
00:04:45,395 --> 00:04:46,830
and the one in the back is me.

77
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:48,198
That's how it feels.

78
00:04:48,198 --> 00:04:50,400
It feels like I'm the one
sitting back there.

79
00:04:53,103 --> 00:04:54,504
(Korean set meal)

80
00:04:55,439 --> 00:04:56,873
It smells amazing.

81
00:04:56,873 --> 00:04:59,943
(Myo Jin's team arrives
at the restaurant.)

82
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:02,012
Myo Jin, you sit there.

83
00:05:07,384 --> 00:05:11,989
(An awkward tension
fills the 2-on-1 date.)

84
00:05:12,556 --> 00:05:16,126
(Silently chugging plain water)

85
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:21,498
I've never eaten a meal like this before,
with two guys sitting across from me.

86
00:05:21,498 --> 00:05:22,265
Of course.

87
00:05:24,234 --> 00:05:25,102
What?

88
00:05:25,469 --> 00:05:26,870
- My goodness.
- Hello, ma'am.

89
00:05:27,804 --> 00:05:29,940
(The sound of a door opening
breaks the awkwardness.)

90
00:05:29,940 --> 00:05:31,775
Hello.

91
00:05:33,343 --> 00:05:35,178
(Myo Jin's mother appears?)

92
00:05:35,178 --> 00:05:37,247
- Her mother?
- Her mother? All of a sudden?

93
00:05:37,247 --> 00:05:40,450
Myo Jin's mother just walked in.

94
00:05:41,285 --> 00:05:42,252
(Startled)

95
00:05:42,252 --> 00:05:43,153
Hello.

96
00:05:43,153 --> 00:05:45,956
- Nice to meet you.
- Hello.

97
00:05:47,024 --> 00:05:48,792
- I missed you.
- Hello, ma'am.

98
00:05:49,893 --> 00:05:51,862
Nice to meet you.

99
00:05:52,696 --> 00:05:54,364
Are you eating together with us?

100
00:05:54,364 --> 00:05:55,299
I guess we are.

101
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:57,634
I see.

102
00:05:57,634 --> 00:05:58,702
That really surprised me.

103
00:05:58,702 --> 00:05:59,603
What a shock.

104
00:06:00,470 --> 00:06:02,572
What were you doing before you came?

105
00:06:02,572 --> 00:06:03,573
What were you doing?

106
00:06:03,573 --> 00:06:05,642
We went on a little trip.

107
00:06:05,642 --> 00:06:07,678
- Really?
- The mothers had a great time together.

108
00:06:07,678 --> 00:06:09,079
Without cameras?

109
00:06:09,079 --> 00:06:10,047
Yeah, without any.

110
00:06:10,047 --> 00:06:11,348
- Completely without?
- None at all.

111
00:06:11,348 --> 00:06:12,883
To our youth.

112
00:06:12,883 --> 00:06:14,518
To our youth.

113
00:06:15,352 --> 00:06:18,055
(For 2 days, the mothers
forgot about their children...)

114
00:06:18,288 --> 00:06:20,090
(and enjoyed themselves.)

115
00:06:20,090 --> 00:06:22,359
They must've had so much fun.

116
00:06:23,427 --> 00:06:27,898
(Then they make a surprise return
to eat with their kids.)

117
00:06:29,466 --> 00:06:31,468
You should've let me enjoy my date.

118
00:06:31,468 --> 00:06:35,439
Why did you turn it
into a matchmaking date?

119
00:06:35,739 --> 00:06:40,143
I was honestly shocked.

120
00:06:41,812 --> 00:06:45,048
It wasn't a date chosen by the men.

121
00:06:45,048 --> 00:06:46,516
Once a choice is made,

122
00:06:46,516 --> 00:06:48,085
they end up meeting the mother together.

123
00:06:48,085 --> 00:06:50,587
- Basically a formal family meeting.
- A family-meeting date.

124
00:06:50,587 --> 00:06:52,089
It's a different concept.

125
00:06:52,089 --> 00:06:53,323
Unbelievable.

126
00:06:53,323 --> 00:06:56,026
We totally forgot
about the mothers for a moment.

127
00:06:56,026 --> 00:06:58,061
Where did they go?

128
00:06:58,495 --> 00:06:59,863
How does it feel
now that two men are here?

129
00:07:01,932 --> 00:07:04,001
It's nice.

130
00:07:04,735 --> 00:07:06,303
Are you sure you can eat with us?

131
00:07:06,303 --> 00:07:07,604
- Yes.
- You're not going to get indigestion?

132
00:07:07,604 --> 00:07:09,106
- No.
- No?

133
00:07:09,106 --> 00:07:11,308
Seeing two men sitting there...

134
00:07:11,308 --> 00:07:12,542
was surprising,

135
00:07:12,542 --> 00:07:14,645
and I was also very grateful.

136
00:07:14,645 --> 00:07:18,382
I had so many mixed emotions.

137
00:07:18,949 --> 00:07:20,684
I was really grateful.

138
00:07:21,518 --> 00:07:23,186
This is totally Mom's style.

139
00:07:23,186 --> 00:07:23,954
That scared me.

140
00:07:23,954 --> 00:07:24,921
Hello, ma'am.

141
00:07:25,489 --> 00:07:27,357
This is totally Mom's style.

142
00:07:27,357 --> 00:07:29,526
(Seung Hak's mother also appears.)

143
00:07:29,526 --> 00:07:30,694
Hello.

144
00:07:31,595 --> 00:07:32,596
Welcome.

145
00:07:32,963 --> 00:07:35,465
You were chosen. You look beautiful.

146
00:07:38,735 --> 00:07:39,670
Nice to see you again.

147
00:07:39,670 --> 00:07:41,805
Yes, it's so nice to see you too.

148
00:07:42,205 --> 00:07:45,976
From start to finish,
you haven't changed your mind.

149
00:07:45,976 --> 00:07:46,877
He really hasn't.

150
00:07:48,745 --> 00:07:50,714
(Se Hoon's mother also appears.)

151
00:07:50,714 --> 00:07:51,949
Welcome.

152
00:07:52,482 --> 00:07:53,250
This way.

153
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:54,284
Welcome.

154
00:07:55,352 --> 00:07:56,320
Hello.

155
00:07:57,054 --> 00:07:58,622
- Mom, this way.
- Over there.

156
00:07:58,622 --> 00:07:59,523
(Bustling)

157
00:07:59,523 --> 00:08:01,158
It's a family meeting.

158
00:08:02,192 --> 00:08:03,627
I guess they all have the same taste.

159
00:08:04,361 --> 00:08:05,929
My son and Se Hoon.

160
00:08:08,298 --> 00:08:09,800
Thank you so much.

161
00:08:12,302 --> 00:08:15,472
Now that two teams
have already chosen one person,

162
00:08:15,472 --> 00:08:16,440
what happens to the remaining one?

163
00:08:18,342 --> 00:08:19,343
I'm worried.

164
00:08:20,010 --> 00:08:21,278
We know exactly how that feels.

165
00:08:21,278 --> 00:08:23,447
You and I were best friends.

166
00:08:23,447 --> 00:08:26,416
So what happens to us now?

167
00:08:27,050 --> 00:08:28,452
Exactly.

168
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,756
Yes! Two pairs of shoes.

169
00:08:35,392 --> 00:08:36,293
Hello.

170
00:08:36,293 --> 00:08:38,095
(Cho Eun Na Rae and Seo Han Gyeol's room)

171
00:08:38,095 --> 00:08:38,929
Hello.

172
00:08:39,363 --> 00:08:40,263
(Overjoyed)

173
00:08:40,263 --> 00:08:42,566
Have you been well? How have you been?

174
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:45,268
Why is my mother being like that?

175
00:08:45,268 --> 00:08:46,803
- I'm nervous.
- Please sit.

176
00:08:46,970 --> 00:08:51,508
The same person was sitting there,
just like always.

177
00:08:51,508 --> 00:08:52,442
And that made me happy.

178
00:08:53,744 --> 00:08:56,880
You're so sweet.

179
00:08:58,215 --> 00:09:00,350
This is exactly the picture I wanted.

180
00:09:00,717 --> 00:09:02,019
You're making us uncomfortable.

181
00:09:02,019 --> 00:09:04,354
I should say this before his mother comes
because she might be upset.

182
00:09:04,354 --> 00:09:05,689
No, my mother wouldn't be upset.

183
00:09:05,689 --> 00:09:08,158
I just love
seeing the two of you together.

184
00:09:08,158 --> 00:09:09,760
Why would his mother be upset?

185
00:09:10,127 --> 00:09:11,395
No, not me.

186
00:09:11,395 --> 00:09:14,431
My mother? She's not upset at all.

187
00:09:14,631 --> 00:09:17,467
Sorry. I'm sorry.

188
00:09:17,467 --> 00:09:18,902
You always say that.

189
00:09:20,437 --> 00:09:23,407
But from his mother's point of view,

190
00:09:23,407 --> 00:09:25,842
since there's quite a big age gap...

191
00:09:25,842 --> 00:09:27,110
Don't.

192
00:09:28,078 --> 00:09:30,981
It's okay.
My mother really won't mind that much.

193
00:09:30,981 --> 00:09:31,882
Really?

194
00:09:32,649 --> 00:09:34,918
I feel like she might mind that a lot.

195
00:09:34,918 --> 00:09:39,122
Let's see
how Han Gyeol's mother will feel.

196
00:09:39,856 --> 00:09:40,958
(Knock, knock)

197
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:42,659
- I think my mother's here.
- Must be his mother.

198
00:09:44,094 --> 00:09:46,330
- Hello .
- Mom.

199
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:47,264
Have you been well?

200
00:09:48,098 --> 00:09:48,899
Hey.

201
00:09:48,899 --> 00:09:49,933
(Han Gyeol's mother arrives,
making Eun Na Rae's mother worried.)

202
00:09:49,933 --> 00:09:51,668
- You're wearing something bright.
- Yeah.

203
00:09:51,668 --> 00:09:52,336
Good choice.

204
00:09:52,336 --> 00:09:53,804
It's nice to meet you.

205
00:09:53,804 --> 00:09:54,738
Nice to meet you.

206
00:09:55,405 --> 00:09:56,740
Hello.

207
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:58,041
Hello.

208
00:09:58,041 --> 00:09:58,909
Please have a seat.

209
00:09:59,376 --> 00:10:03,347
I never imagined we'd meet like this.

210
00:10:03,347 --> 00:10:04,548
Neither did I.

211
00:10:04,815 --> 00:10:07,150
They said the man made the choice.

212
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:08,819
Since Han Gyeol was the one choosing,

213
00:10:10,087 --> 00:10:12,189
given his personality,

214
00:10:13,390 --> 00:10:17,828
rather than meeting
several people in a short time,

215
00:10:17,828 --> 00:10:22,666
"Even focusing on one person
isn't enough time."

216
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:24,234
He probably thought like this.

217
00:10:25,135 --> 00:10:30,807
So he likely just followed his feelings
and kept choosing the same person.

218
00:10:32,042 --> 00:10:32,976
(Kim Hyun Jin and Jang Min Cheol's room)

219
00:10:32,976 --> 00:10:34,978
- Hello.
- Hello.

220
00:10:34,978 --> 00:10:37,414
Welcome. I'll hang your bag for you.

221
00:10:37,414 --> 00:10:38,515
Mom, it's so good to see you.

222
00:10:38,515 --> 00:10:40,183
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

223
00:10:41,184 --> 00:10:43,920
- Welcome.
- Hello.

224
00:10:44,988 --> 00:10:46,657
- Shall I close the door?
- Yes.

225
00:10:48,225 --> 00:10:49,893
Nice to meet you.

226
00:10:49,893 --> 00:10:52,763
It's so nice to see you
after such a long time.

227
00:10:52,763 --> 00:10:53,597
(My goodness)

228
00:10:53,597 --> 00:10:55,098
Two nights and three days.

229
00:10:55,565 --> 00:10:58,302
Since that secret meeting,

230
00:10:58,302 --> 00:11:00,137
- it really has been a long time.
- It really has.

231
00:11:00,137 --> 00:11:04,808
They say Min Cheol and Hyun Jin...

232
00:11:04,808 --> 00:11:06,777
were both the mothers' picks.

233
00:11:06,777 --> 00:11:08,578
Apparently,
the mothers really liked the two.

234
00:11:08,578 --> 00:11:11,648
His mother liked her,
and her mother liked him.

235
00:11:14,851 --> 00:11:21,358
(Meanwhile,
Jin Joo arrives at the restaurant alone.)

236
00:11:31,435 --> 00:11:34,237
Seeing her sitting alone again today,
her mother must feel so heartbroken.

237
00:11:34,237 --> 00:11:36,306
You don't have to feel too discouraged.

238
00:11:36,306 --> 00:11:37,741
- That's true.
- In the end,

239
00:11:37,741 --> 00:11:39,476
it all comes down to the final moment.

240
00:11:40,844 --> 00:11:41,778
Yeah!

241
00:11:41,778 --> 00:11:46,316
(The noise from the next room
stirs her emotions.)

242
00:11:49,019 --> 00:11:53,123
(Jin Joo's mother appears.)

243
00:11:54,291 --> 00:11:55,592
So it's just the two of us eating?

244
00:11:56,326 --> 00:11:57,227
Sit there.

245
00:12:01,198 --> 00:12:02,265
Have you been okay?

246
00:12:02,265 --> 00:12:03,467
How were you, Mom?

247
00:12:03,467 --> 00:12:05,435
I was fine. I rested comfortably.

248
00:12:05,435 --> 00:12:07,271
I was worried, Mom.
You didn't even take your bag.

249
00:12:07,271 --> 00:12:08,538
How about your health?

250
00:12:09,273 --> 00:12:10,107
I'm fine.

251
00:12:10,107 --> 00:12:10,907
Did you cry?

252
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,514
Don't cry.

253
00:12:21,551 --> 00:12:22,586
You must've been really upset.

254
00:12:26,456 --> 00:12:28,825
What about breakfast?
Did you eat this morning?

255
00:12:29,593 --> 00:12:30,594
You didn't?

256
00:12:33,964 --> 00:12:35,232
Why are you crying?

257
00:12:35,799 --> 00:12:38,702
(Heartbroken)

258
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,908
What if I can't get married?

259
00:12:44,908 --> 00:12:46,476
Then don't. Just live with me.

260
00:12:46,476 --> 00:12:48,512
Seeing things here,

261
00:12:48,512 --> 00:12:51,581
I realized you were still too young
to get married.

262
00:12:51,982 --> 00:12:53,050
No one chose me,

263
00:12:53,050 --> 00:12:54,551
but it's not the zero votes
that hurt, but...

264
00:12:54,551 --> 00:12:56,520
What matters
is protecting your mental strength.

265
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:58,755
Out in the real world,

266
00:12:58,755 --> 00:13:01,391
have you ever not been chosen even once?

267
00:13:01,391 --> 00:13:02,693
When you were dating outside?

268
00:13:02,693 --> 00:13:05,095
I mean outside of here, outside this camp.

269
00:13:05,095 --> 00:13:08,165
You're a great and amazing person.

270
00:13:08,165 --> 00:13:09,900
Don't let this shake you so much.

271
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:13,470
I should be honest with you
about that day.

272
00:13:13,470 --> 00:13:15,272
On the day of the self-introductions,

273
00:13:15,272 --> 00:13:19,209
I wrote about you more honestly
than the other mothers did, right?

274
00:13:20,611 --> 00:13:21,645
You were sorry about that, right?

275
00:13:22,012 --> 00:13:22,980
No.

276
00:13:22,980 --> 00:13:25,282
When you told me "I'm sorry," I cried.

277
00:13:26,583 --> 00:13:28,485
When did I say I was sorry?

278
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,655
Mom, you must be embarrassed
because of me. I'm sorry.

279
00:13:31,655 --> 00:13:32,623
- No.
- Are you okay?

280
00:13:32,623 --> 00:13:33,423
Yeah.

281
00:13:33,423 --> 00:13:35,826
Just the fact
that you had the courage to come here...

282
00:13:35,826 --> 00:13:37,995
Haven't you thought about this?

283
00:13:37,995 --> 00:13:39,129
(A daughter blaming herself
for not being chosen)

284
00:13:39,329 --> 00:13:41,031
Maybe I shouldn't have come at all.

285
00:13:41,031 --> 00:13:47,738
(A mother whose heart aches watching her)

286
00:13:49,072 --> 00:13:52,109
When you said you were sorry,
that really upset me.

287
00:13:52,109 --> 00:13:53,110
Did I say I was sorry?

288
00:13:53,110 --> 00:13:55,112
Yes, you said, "Mom, I'm sorry."

289
00:13:55,479 --> 00:13:56,513
In the room.

290
00:13:56,513 --> 00:13:58,515
(Hoping her daughter
won't blame herself today)

291
00:13:58,882 --> 00:14:00,350
Are you okay right now?

292
00:14:02,419 --> 00:14:03,287
I'm not okay.

293
00:14:03,287 --> 00:14:04,421
Of course, I'm not okay.

294
00:14:07,024 --> 00:14:09,159
It's natural to feel like crying
in front of Mom.

295
00:14:09,826 --> 00:14:11,461
Don't be so hard on yourself.

296
00:14:12,062 --> 00:14:14,731
- She's still young, that's why.
- She shouldn't give up already.

297
00:14:15,032 --> 00:14:18,135
This isn't a final decision.

298
00:14:18,135 --> 00:14:20,671
Of course, she knows that,

299
00:14:20,671 --> 00:14:22,572
but from a woman's perspective,

300
00:14:22,572 --> 00:14:25,976
not being chosen feels...

301
00:14:25,976 --> 00:14:28,211
How can anyone be chosen every time?

302
00:14:29,012 --> 00:14:30,948
How can you always be picked?

303
00:14:30,948 --> 00:14:36,486
And since her mother experienced that
with her twice in a row,

304
00:14:36,486 --> 00:14:39,523
that probably made it
even harder for Jin Joo.

305
00:14:39,523 --> 00:14:41,124
- Here.
- Thank you.

306
00:14:41,124 --> 00:14:42,125
Please enjoy your meal.

307
00:14:42,592 --> 00:14:44,561
Hyun Jin, serve Ms. Kang.

308
00:14:46,396 --> 00:14:48,999
I want to give her the big piece.

309
00:14:48,999 --> 00:14:49,800
That line.

310
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,402
- Hyun Jin is doing an amazing job.
- She really is.

311
00:14:52,402 --> 00:14:53,604
She's so good at those things.

312
00:14:53,604 --> 00:14:54,671
She's doing great.

313
00:14:55,906 --> 00:14:58,008
I want to give her the big piece.

314
00:14:58,008 --> 00:14:59,142
(She picks the king-size rib.)

315
00:14:59,142 --> 00:15:00,344
She might not look so,

316
00:15:00,344 --> 00:15:02,679
but Hyuh Jin is very good with elders.

317
00:15:02,679 --> 00:15:03,814
Really?

318
00:15:03,814 --> 00:15:06,083
I've talked to her, right?

319
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:08,151
I can tell.

320
00:15:08,151 --> 00:15:11,421
When I first saw Hyun Jin,

321
00:15:11,421 --> 00:15:13,824
she gave off
a "Korean eldest daughter" vibe.

322
00:15:15,058 --> 00:15:16,994
I raised my three kids...

323
00:15:16,994 --> 00:15:19,296
pretty strictly, almost Spartan-style.

324
00:15:19,296 --> 00:15:20,797
So my kids are all...

325
00:15:20,797 --> 00:15:25,369
very sharp and capable.

326
00:15:26,270 --> 00:15:30,741
She's good-looking
and very capable in real life too.

327
00:15:30,741 --> 00:15:31,875
There's nothing lacking.

328
00:15:31,875 --> 00:15:34,144
She's very capable.

329
00:15:34,878 --> 00:15:37,714
Like I said before,

330
00:15:38,548 --> 00:15:40,117
I personally like people
who are knowledgeable.

331
00:15:41,752 --> 00:15:44,221
- Knowledgeable?
- He went to Seoul National University.

332
00:15:44,221 --> 00:15:47,324
In terms of knowledge, he's top-tier.

333
00:15:47,591 --> 00:15:49,326
I personally like people
who are knowledgeable.

334
00:15:50,494 --> 00:15:53,463
I personally like people
who are academically strong.

335
00:15:53,463 --> 00:15:54,398
Is that so?

336
00:15:55,299 --> 00:15:58,135
It's not just about academic background.

337
00:15:58,135 --> 00:16:01,405
I like that too,

338
00:16:01,405 --> 00:16:03,807
but I also look at character
and responsibility,

339
00:16:03,807 --> 00:16:07,144
and whether someone is thoughtful.

340
00:16:07,144 --> 00:16:10,380
So that's how you see Min Cheol?
Thank you.

341
00:16:10,747 --> 00:16:12,683
(Kim Myo Jin, Lee Seung Hak,
and Moon Se Hoon's room)

342
00:16:12,683 --> 00:16:14,518
I'll serve you.

343
00:16:18,355 --> 00:16:19,189
Just a little, please.

344
00:16:19,189 --> 00:16:20,524
Okay, enjoy.

345
00:16:20,524 --> 00:16:21,959
- Thank you.
- Sure.

346
00:16:23,093 --> 00:16:26,096
I think Myo Jin has pretty generous hands.

347
00:16:27,497 --> 00:16:28,999
How she scoops
the soybean paste soup shows.

348
00:16:31,301 --> 00:16:36,907
But honestly,
I'm not very good at cooking.

349
00:16:36,907 --> 00:16:38,408
That always worries me.

350
00:16:38,408 --> 00:16:40,177
My son cooks well.

351
00:16:40,177 --> 00:16:42,279
Cooking is...

352
00:16:42,279 --> 00:16:43,246
You don't need to worry about that.

353
00:16:43,246 --> 00:16:44,848
It's okay if you can't cook.

354
00:16:44,848 --> 00:16:46,216
You can learn after you get married.

355
00:16:46,216 --> 00:16:47,284
That's also true.

356
00:16:47,551 --> 00:16:49,386
The two men are just eating quietly.

357
00:16:50,921 --> 00:16:52,356
You can learn after you get married.

358
00:16:52,356 --> 00:16:53,390
That's also true.

359
00:16:53,824 --> 00:16:55,692
Still, it's nice when a man can cook.

360
00:16:55,692 --> 00:16:58,161
Well, that would be nice, but my son...

361
00:16:58,161 --> 00:17:01,465
is not picky with food, so it's fine.

362
00:17:01,465 --> 00:17:02,232
Is that so?

363
00:17:03,033 --> 00:17:04,635
Being good at cooking is a plus.

364
00:17:06,436 --> 00:17:07,471
(An unexpected loss)

365
00:17:07,471 --> 00:17:08,672
Please eat up.

366
00:17:08,672 --> 00:17:10,207
- Yes.
- My goodness.

367
00:17:11,041 --> 00:17:13,010
The mothers have gone
into competition mode.

368
00:17:13,343 --> 00:17:15,712
I had eel yesterday.

369
00:17:15,712 --> 00:17:18,148
How did you eat eel yesterday?
Did you go out?

370
00:17:18,148 --> 00:17:20,550
Yes, during our lunch date.

371
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:21,752
Did you keep going out on dates?

372
00:17:21,752 --> 00:17:23,253
- I see.
- Yes.

373
00:17:23,253 --> 00:17:24,821
Who was your lunch date with?

374
00:17:25,856 --> 00:17:26,890
Myo Jin.

375
00:17:26,890 --> 00:17:27,991
Myo Jin, again?

376
00:17:28,925 --> 00:17:29,860
This is basically decided then.

377
00:17:31,695 --> 00:17:32,629
What are you talking about?

378
00:17:32,629 --> 00:17:33,864
Isn't that great?

379
00:17:33,864 --> 00:17:35,265
That's how it looks to me.

380
00:17:35,666 --> 00:17:37,401
Your houses are close too.

381
00:17:37,401 --> 00:17:38,435
Ours is close as well.

382
00:17:39,136 --> 00:17:42,773
If we sit down,
it's practically their place.

383
00:17:42,773 --> 00:17:44,341
My son will move closer there too.

384
00:17:44,341 --> 00:17:47,110
(About to bleed from the ears)

385
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:48,946
Are you two fighting?
Mom, what are you doing?

386
00:17:50,781 --> 00:17:52,282
She's very proactive.

387
00:17:53,083 --> 00:17:53,917
But...

388
00:17:53,917 --> 00:17:57,287
Se Hoon's mother...

389
00:17:57,287 --> 00:17:59,556
was really staring me down...

390
00:18:01,558 --> 00:18:02,559
like I was a serious rival.

391
00:18:03,627 --> 00:18:05,395
Since Seung Hak likes Myo Jin,

392
00:18:06,263 --> 00:18:07,597
I'm just giving it a shot.

393
00:18:07,597 --> 00:18:08,832
I'm jumping right in.

394
00:18:10,367 --> 00:18:14,538
Just a few hours ago,
she was like a close sister...

395
00:18:14,538 --> 00:18:16,073
I laughed with,

396
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:18,575
and now she's my rival.

397
00:18:18,575 --> 00:18:19,443
No.

398
00:18:22,079 --> 00:18:22,779
(Cho Eun Na Rae and Seo Han Gyeol's room)

399
00:18:22,779 --> 00:18:23,847
Thank you so much.

400
00:18:23,847 --> 00:18:27,017
You don't have to thank me.
I came because I wanted to.

401
00:18:27,017 --> 00:18:29,386
- I'm a bit sorry to my daughter, though.
- Why?

402
00:18:29,386 --> 00:18:32,656
I honestly thought
it would be just the two of you eating.

403
00:18:32,656 --> 00:18:33,724
You did?

404
00:18:33,724 --> 00:18:36,093
I really did! But...

405
00:18:36,093 --> 00:18:38,528
I walked in and saw two pairs of shoes.

406
00:18:38,528 --> 00:18:40,097
So from outside I was already like,

407
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:43,667
"This is awesome! Unbelievable!"

408
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:45,502
Like this.

409
00:18:45,502 --> 00:18:47,671
I'll tell you about my daughter.

410
00:18:47,671 --> 00:18:50,140
When my daughter dates someone,

411
00:18:50,140 --> 00:18:52,075
she's very affectionate and cute.

412
00:18:52,075 --> 00:18:53,610
- Almost like a baby.
- That's true.

413
00:18:53,610 --> 00:18:55,579
I do have a childlike side.

414
00:18:55,579 --> 00:18:57,281
She really does.

415
00:18:57,281 --> 00:18:58,649
- I can really feel that.
- Really?

416
00:18:58,649 --> 00:19:00,284
She doesn't look very happy.

417
00:19:00,284 --> 00:19:02,786
As she gets a year or two older,

418
00:19:02,786 --> 00:19:06,490
her way of thinking seems to change a bit.

419
00:19:06,490 --> 00:19:09,059
So her father keeps saying,

420
00:19:09,059 --> 00:19:12,229
she should marry before it's too late.

421
00:19:12,229 --> 00:19:13,797
(Sigh)

422
00:19:13,997 --> 00:19:16,867
When does he say she should marry?

423
00:19:16,867 --> 00:19:19,870
He says even tomorrow would be fine,

424
00:19:19,870 --> 00:19:21,805
or next month would be great.

425
00:19:21,805 --> 00:19:25,442
He'd welcome it,
but it's not something you can force.

426
00:19:25,442 --> 00:19:29,413
But she wasn't thinking
about marriage at all,

427
00:19:29,413 --> 00:19:31,648
so we just read the room
and didn't bring it up.

428
00:19:31,648 --> 00:19:33,050
That's why.

429
00:19:34,217 --> 00:19:37,854
So I'm really grateful for this.

430
00:19:37,854 --> 00:19:38,622
Even now,

431
00:19:38,622 --> 00:19:40,057
I have water in my cup.

432
00:19:40,057 --> 00:19:41,391
Thanks.

433
00:19:41,391 --> 00:19:43,827
She doesn't look very happy.

434
00:19:44,795 --> 00:19:48,265
My mother was so emotional...

435
00:19:48,999 --> 00:19:51,635
and so grateful that Han Gyeol came,

436
00:19:51,635 --> 00:19:53,637
almost like, "Thank you so much."

437
00:19:53,637 --> 00:19:56,540
"We're the weaker side,
and you're the stronger side."

438
00:19:56,540 --> 00:19:58,408
That kind of dynamic.

439
00:20:00,010 --> 00:20:02,913
Age is a separate issue.

440
00:20:02,913 --> 00:20:05,415
I don't want
a relationship to start like that.

441
00:20:05,949 --> 00:20:07,517
Why be in a relationship like that?

442
00:20:08,385 --> 00:20:11,888
I'm not desperate
to date a younger man, either.

443
00:20:11,888 --> 00:20:13,256
So I don't want it to be that way.

444
00:20:14,324 --> 00:20:16,893
(Eun Na Rae is deep in thought.)

445
00:20:16,893 --> 00:20:17,761
I see.

446
00:20:18,729 --> 00:20:20,163
Is there anything you're curious about?

447
00:20:20,697 --> 00:20:22,165
Well...

448
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:25,369
Anything, really.

449
00:20:25,369 --> 00:20:26,770
It suddenly feels uncomfortable.

450
00:20:28,505 --> 00:20:30,307
There's nothing
to feel uncomfortable about.

451
00:20:30,307 --> 00:20:33,143
But Ms. Kwon doesn't seem like the type
to feel awkward in situations like this.

452
00:20:33,143 --> 00:20:34,544
My mother...

453
00:20:34,544 --> 00:20:36,313
is great.

454
00:20:36,313 --> 00:20:37,581
She does seem that way.

455
00:20:40,350 --> 00:20:42,853
She doesn't look happy.

456
00:20:43,620 --> 00:20:45,389
She seems really uncomfortable.

457
00:20:47,924 --> 00:20:50,327
But why does this feel so uncomfortable?

458
00:20:50,327 --> 00:20:51,561
What does? The situation?

459
00:20:51,561 --> 00:20:53,764
I don't know what to do.

460
00:20:53,764 --> 00:20:54,531
Yeah.

461
00:20:54,531 --> 00:20:57,601
And since we weren't told in advance,
even my outfit feels a bit off.

462
00:20:57,601 --> 00:20:58,502
Exactly.

463
00:20:58,502 --> 00:20:59,703
But it's okay.

464
00:20:59,703 --> 00:21:01,138
Still.

465
00:21:01,138 --> 00:21:05,809
Han Gyeol wants me
to be friendly and courteous.

466
00:21:06,510 --> 00:21:08,612
That's the kind of person he likes.

467
00:21:08,612 --> 00:21:09,346
With whom?

468
00:21:09,346 --> 00:21:11,348
With his mother.

469
00:21:11,348 --> 00:21:14,251
I see.

470
00:21:14,251 --> 00:21:18,555
But whether it's toward
their partner's mother or anyone else,

471
00:21:18,555 --> 00:21:20,657
there are people who are just naturally
friendly and courteous, right?

472
00:21:20,657 --> 00:21:22,125
He likes that, and he really...

473
00:21:22,125 --> 00:21:22,926
That's me.

474
00:21:22,926 --> 00:21:24,695
He really values that a lot.

475
00:21:24,695 --> 00:21:25,529
That's exactly me.

476
00:21:25,929 --> 00:21:27,731
So, what about that?

477
00:21:28,498 --> 00:21:30,667
Why are you suddenly saying that's you?

478
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:31,468
Just...

479
00:21:32,569 --> 00:21:34,204
Then go marry him.

480
00:21:34,204 --> 00:21:36,373
I'm just saying that's me.

481
00:21:38,275 --> 00:21:40,110
We're talking about me right now.

482
00:21:41,945 --> 00:21:43,046
Seriously.

483
00:21:45,515 --> 00:21:51,288
(Cho Eun Na Rae is hurt.)

484
00:21:53,757 --> 00:21:55,525
Was there anyone else...

485
00:21:55,525 --> 00:21:58,228
Eun Na Rae might have wanted to see more?

486
00:21:58,228 --> 00:21:59,396
She said there wasn't.

487
00:21:59,396 --> 00:22:00,764
- There wasn't?
- No.

488
00:22:01,565 --> 00:22:04,234
But even today, it was still enjoyable.

489
00:22:04,234 --> 00:22:06,136
The dinner felt comfortable and easy...

490
00:22:06,136 --> 00:22:08,105
being with her mother.

491
00:22:08,672 --> 00:22:09,973
She seems like such a nice person.

492
00:22:11,775 --> 00:22:18,081
For me, it felt like a situation
that could actually be a bit difficult.

493
00:22:18,081 --> 00:22:20,250
Being comfortable is nice,

494
00:22:21,018 --> 00:22:23,620
but I started wondering,
"Is this really right?"

495
00:22:23,620 --> 00:22:26,156
If it's uncomfortable, does that mean
the conversation gets better?

496
00:22:26,156 --> 00:22:28,158
It's not about having
"better" conversations.

497
00:22:28,158 --> 00:22:31,995
I'm saying, is it okay to move forward
based only on feeling comfortable?

498
00:22:31,995 --> 00:22:32,896
I mean...

499
00:22:32,896 --> 00:22:36,466
If we're going to talk more
about it now...

500
00:22:36,466 --> 00:22:38,168
What did you want to talk about there?

501
00:22:38,168 --> 00:22:40,971
The age gap, for example.

502
00:22:40,971 --> 00:22:42,673
I said I'd handle that myself.

503
00:22:42,673 --> 00:22:46,243
Those issues.

504
00:22:46,777 --> 00:22:49,446
What does talking about that
with Eun Na Rae's mother actually solve?

505
00:22:49,746 --> 00:22:50,747
With me...

506
00:22:50,747 --> 00:22:53,917
It's not a conversation
to make a decision or reach a conclusion.

507
00:22:53,917 --> 00:22:55,118
It's just that...

508
00:22:55,118 --> 00:22:58,055
Isn't it okay to at least ask,

509
00:22:58,055 --> 00:22:59,389
"There's an age gap.
How do you feel about that?"

510
00:22:59,389 --> 00:23:01,792
They already know that, of course.

511
00:23:01,792 --> 00:23:02,559
Yeah.

512
00:23:02,559 --> 00:23:05,429
That's something
I want to take responsibility for.

513
00:23:05,429 --> 00:23:08,498
I want to be the one to judge it.

514
00:23:08,498 --> 00:23:10,734
Honestly, you can't really influence me...

515
00:23:10,734 --> 00:23:12,402
that much anyway about that issue, Mom.

516
00:23:12,402 --> 00:23:13,103
I know.

517
00:23:13,103 --> 00:23:15,973
Then why does it feel like, on that issue,

518
00:23:15,973 --> 00:23:19,610
you're so uneasy and...

519
00:23:19,610 --> 00:23:21,345
I'm not "uneasy."

520
00:23:21,345 --> 00:23:24,047
Well, but about those concerns...

521
00:23:24,047 --> 00:23:27,951
- I know you can't just not mention them.
- Even if I can't influence you,

522
00:23:28,652 --> 00:23:31,455
bringing the mother into this means...

523
00:23:31,455 --> 00:23:33,490
I do have a say.

524
00:23:33,490 --> 00:23:37,094
The decision is yours in the end,

525
00:23:37,094 --> 00:23:38,695
but it's about giving me a chance too.

526
00:23:38,695 --> 00:23:41,798
It's bout giving your mother
a chance as well.

527
00:23:41,798 --> 00:23:45,602
Of course.
It's not that I'm ignoring you, Mom.

528
00:23:45,602 --> 00:23:50,674
If I hadn't already thought
about the things you worry about,

529
00:23:52,209 --> 00:23:54,611
then I might ask your opinion.

530
00:23:55,212 --> 00:23:59,216
But I've already been thinking
about those concerns.

531
00:23:59,216 --> 00:24:01,151
It's not like I'm unaware of them.

532
00:24:01,151 --> 00:24:02,619
Yes, you said you know.

533
00:24:02,619 --> 00:24:05,055
I know, and I'm conflicted too.

534
00:24:05,989 --> 00:24:07,758
So should I just not say anything, then?

535
00:24:07,758 --> 00:24:08,959
That's exactly right.

536
00:24:08,959 --> 00:24:10,160
Should I really not say anything?

537
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,128
Yes.

538
00:24:11,128 --> 00:24:12,229
That's what I think.

539
00:24:13,664 --> 00:24:14,831
Is there really a need?

540
00:24:17,868 --> 00:24:19,202
This is upsetting.

541
00:24:23,273 --> 00:24:27,244
(The mood turns cold in an instant.)

542
00:24:27,244 --> 00:24:32,783
If I had to read
Han Gyeol's feelings exactly,

543
00:24:32,783 --> 00:24:35,852
it's that his mother rubbed him
the wrong way in that moment.

544
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:38,555
She didn't really respond much.

545
00:24:38,555 --> 00:24:40,390
Even if it's just on the surface.

546
00:24:40,390 --> 00:24:42,192
"You may not like it,"

547
00:24:42,192 --> 00:24:44,995
"but you could at least be polite
on the surface."

548
00:24:44,995 --> 00:24:49,266
"So why did you have to make it
so obvious you didn't like it, Mom?"

549
00:24:49,666 --> 00:24:51,368
That's what he's talking about right now.

550
00:24:51,535 --> 00:24:53,804
From a mother's point of view...

551
00:24:53,804 --> 00:24:55,339
- She's worried.
- Right.

552
00:24:55,339 --> 00:25:00,677
I understand both sides,
the son's and the mother's.

553
00:25:01,411 --> 00:25:02,946
It feels comfortable
riding in my son's car.

554
00:25:06,617 --> 00:25:09,620
I thought it would just be a light date,

555
00:25:09,620 --> 00:25:11,288
just some time to talk.

556
00:25:11,288 --> 00:25:14,625
Yesterday, I gave all my picks to Jin Joo.

557
00:25:14,625 --> 00:25:16,159
I see.

558
00:25:16,827 --> 00:25:17,828
I see.

559
00:25:17,828 --> 00:25:20,597
So I wanted to talk more
with someone else,

560
00:25:20,597 --> 00:25:22,799
but this matchmaking date vibe...

561
00:25:23,667 --> 00:25:24,434
I like it.

562
00:25:24,434 --> 00:25:26,637
If I really went on a matchmaking date,
it would've felt like this.

563
00:25:26,637 --> 00:25:27,971
That's right.

564
00:25:27,971 --> 00:25:31,275
Still, what I'm grateful for is that
the two people I'm interested in...

565
00:25:31,942 --> 00:25:34,578
- Two people.
- are also interested in me.

566
00:25:35,178 --> 00:25:37,114
I'm grateful for that.

567
00:25:37,114 --> 00:25:38,181
Right.

568
00:25:39,483 --> 00:25:42,619
But for some reason,
Jin Joo keeps coming to mind.

569
00:25:42,619 --> 00:25:43,687
I see.

570
00:25:43,687 --> 00:25:48,525
Because honestly,
Jin Joo is the type I usually like.

571
00:25:48,959 --> 00:25:52,162
That's why I chose her
in the first impression vote.

572
00:25:52,162 --> 00:25:52,963
Right.

573
00:25:53,196 --> 00:25:54,831
I like that kind of gentle and soft...

574
00:25:54,831 --> 00:25:57,534
Well, she's not actually
gentle and soft in personally.

575
00:25:57,534 --> 00:25:59,903
Jin Joo isn't exactly gentle,
but she's pure.

576
00:25:59,903 --> 00:26:01,705
At least that's how she feels to me.

577
00:26:01,705 --> 00:26:03,240
She's pure.

578
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:04,207
She's honest.

579
00:26:04,207 --> 00:26:07,311
She doesn't say things she doesn't mean.
No empty words.

580
00:26:07,311 --> 00:26:08,845
To some people, that might come across as,

581
00:26:09,613 --> 00:26:12,349
"Why is she so blunt?"

582
00:26:12,349 --> 00:26:14,318
But to me, instead of that,

583
00:26:14,318 --> 00:26:18,455
it feels like she only says
what's honest and sincere.

584
00:26:18,455 --> 00:26:20,524
That's how it feels to me.

585
00:26:20,524 --> 00:26:22,059
Right.

586
00:26:22,059 --> 00:26:23,193
She doesn't sugarcoat things.

587
00:26:23,193 --> 00:26:24,628
She doesn't sugarcoat.

588
00:26:24,628 --> 00:26:26,897
People usually calculate how they'll come
across and act accordingly.

589
00:26:26,897 --> 00:26:28,198
Right.

590
00:26:28,198 --> 00:26:31,268
But she doesn't do that.
She's completely immersed in this show.

591
00:26:31,268 --> 00:26:33,437
So she gets stressed,

592
00:26:33,437 --> 00:26:36,139
and it really takes a toll on her.
Her stomach keeps hurting.

593
00:26:36,139 --> 00:26:37,341
(Min Cheol pours out his feelings
about Jin Joo to his mother.)

594
00:26:38,075 --> 00:26:42,012
So Jin Joo gives me this feeling.

595
00:26:42,012 --> 00:26:43,213
Should I describe it
as a paternal instinct?

596
00:26:43,947 --> 00:26:48,085
I just want to take care of her
and cherish her.

597
00:26:48,085 --> 00:26:48,885
I see.

598
00:26:49,886 --> 00:26:51,121
On the way to the restaurant,

599
00:26:52,322 --> 00:26:56,059
I happened to see Jin Joo getting out of
a car with a really downcast expression.

600
00:26:56,827 --> 00:26:57,828
By chance.

601
00:26:58,862 --> 00:27:00,530
And that image just stuck with me.

602
00:27:01,231 --> 00:27:02,699
I'd already been thinking about it...

603
00:27:03,433 --> 00:27:04,434
for a while now.

604
00:27:04,434 --> 00:27:07,471
(He spots Jin Joo.)

605
00:27:08,205 --> 00:27:14,811
(Jin Joo's expression stayed on his mind
throughout the meal.)

606
00:27:16,113 --> 00:27:17,381
Wait.

607
00:27:17,381 --> 00:27:21,285
He had that meeting-the-parents-style meal
with Hyun Jin and her mother,

608
00:27:21,785 --> 00:27:24,921
but his feelings seemed...

609
00:27:24,921 --> 00:27:26,657
to have changed to Jin Joo.

610
00:27:26,657 --> 00:27:32,095
That's what I felt in the car.

611
00:27:32,863 --> 00:27:34,898
So I thought I needed
to think things through...

612
00:27:34,898 --> 00:27:37,434
and said, "Let's talk more
back at the lodging," and came back.

613
00:27:40,270 --> 00:27:44,541
I keep worrying about
how hurt Jin Joo must feel.

614
00:27:44,541 --> 00:27:45,509
Of course.

615
00:27:45,809 --> 00:27:48,879
What if she's sick again today?

616
00:27:48,879 --> 00:27:49,780
Exactly.

617
00:27:51,181 --> 00:27:53,550
So realistically speaking, for example,

618
00:27:54,251 --> 00:27:56,386
if you choose Hyun Jin,

619
00:27:56,386 --> 00:27:59,823
there's no issue with dating her.

620
00:27:59,823 --> 00:28:02,025
She lives in Gangdong-gu.

621
00:28:02,025 --> 00:28:02,893
It's really close.

622
00:28:02,893 --> 00:28:05,262
But if you choose Jin Joo,

623
00:28:05,262 --> 00:28:07,130
you'd have to go back and forth
to Pyeongtaek.

624
00:28:07,130 --> 00:28:08,966
And one concern I have is this.

625
00:28:09,866 --> 00:28:12,035
Human emotions don't work like this.

626
00:28:12,035 --> 00:28:15,372
Feeling nothing Monday through Friday,

627
00:28:15,372 --> 00:28:18,008
then suddenly being in love
on the weekend.

628
00:28:18,809 --> 00:28:22,512
So the question is whether my feelings
are strong enough...

629
00:28:22,512 --> 00:28:24,147
- Right.
- to overcome those real-life obstacles.

630
00:28:24,147 --> 00:28:26,817
That's the question.

631
00:28:28,185 --> 00:28:30,087
So while I still have time,

632
00:28:30,087 --> 00:28:31,421
I want to tell her honestly...

633
00:28:33,590 --> 00:28:37,327
why I didn't choose her this morning.

634
00:28:38,095 --> 00:28:39,429
So I want to talk with her now.

635
00:28:39,429 --> 00:28:40,297
Do it.

636
00:28:40,297 --> 00:28:42,933
But she might not want to talk to me.

637
00:28:42,933 --> 00:28:44,067
She may be too hurt.

638
00:28:44,067 --> 00:28:45,235
Then what do you do?

639
00:28:46,903 --> 00:28:49,039
(Min Cheol smiles
at the thought of seeing Jin Joo.)

640
00:28:49,039 --> 00:28:50,607
How would I comfort her?

641
00:28:52,309 --> 00:28:54,544
I talked things through...

642
00:28:54,544 --> 00:28:57,214
about all kinds of things with my mother.

643
00:28:58,348 --> 00:29:00,651
"I don't know,
but Jin Joo just keeps coming to mind."

644
00:29:02,219 --> 00:29:04,821
"In the end, I want to go to Jin Joo."

645
00:29:05,088 --> 00:29:09,126
I feel this urge
to work through those real-life issues.

646
00:29:09,126 --> 00:29:13,397
That's when I realized,
"I really do like Jin Joo."

647
00:29:13,397 --> 00:29:14,831
Talking with my mother
actually made it clearer.

648
00:29:15,799 --> 00:29:19,436
If you can't stop thinking about someone
even when you avoid them, that's real.

649
00:29:19,436 --> 00:29:20,037
Right?

650
00:29:20,037 --> 00:29:21,505
- You need some distance to realize.
- Exactly.

651
00:29:22,940 --> 00:29:26,343
I should change
into the cardigan Jin Joo likes.

652
00:29:26,343 --> 00:29:27,311
Okay.

653
00:29:27,878 --> 00:29:29,646
There's a cardigan Jin Joo likes.

654
00:29:29,646 --> 00:29:30,981
- That one?
- Yeah.

655
00:29:31,915 --> 00:29:32,849
So that's the one.

656
00:29:32,849 --> 00:29:33,850
I'll do it.

657
00:29:33,850 --> 00:29:35,118
Look at you.

658
00:29:35,118 --> 00:29:36,320
Yes.

659
00:29:37,187 --> 00:29:38,755
- I'll be back.
- Yeah.

660
00:29:41,792 --> 00:29:46,430
(Meanwhile,
Jin Joo lies down at the lodging.)

661
00:29:46,430 --> 00:29:47,831
It's hard to keep my expression together.

662
00:29:48,265 --> 00:29:50,000
You don't have to anymore.

663
00:29:51,969 --> 00:29:54,004
Jin Joo, don't be like that.

664
00:29:54,004 --> 00:29:54,871
Okay.

665
00:29:55,272 --> 00:29:56,540
But there's really nothing to do.

666
00:29:56,540 --> 00:29:58,709
You can go out.

667
00:30:00,143 --> 00:30:00,844
No today.

668
00:30:00,844 --> 00:30:02,279
I went out a lot yesterday.

669
00:30:02,279 --> 00:30:03,080
Really?

670
00:30:03,947 --> 00:30:06,283
Just let it go, Jin Joo.

671
00:30:06,817 --> 00:30:09,386
I guess life hasn't been
too rough until now. This feels hard.

672
00:30:09,386 --> 00:30:12,689
Of course. You're still young.

673
00:30:14,358 --> 00:30:15,459
You shouldn't be dealing
with hardships already.

674
00:30:15,459 --> 00:30:17,461
She's never been
in a situation like this before.

675
00:30:17,461 --> 00:30:19,129
If she didn't like someone,
she just came home.

676
00:30:22,532 --> 00:30:23,433
Hello, ma'am.

677
00:30:24,368 --> 00:30:25,936
Min Cheol.

678
00:30:25,936 --> 00:30:27,304
Hello, ma'am.

679
00:30:27,304 --> 00:30:29,106
Nice to see you.

680
00:30:29,106 --> 00:30:30,007
Did you have a good meal?

681
00:30:30,007 --> 00:30:31,575
Yeah, it was good.

682
00:30:31,575 --> 00:30:33,844
(Hesitating)

683
00:30:35,312 --> 00:30:36,413
Did you have a good time?

684
00:30:36,413 --> 00:30:37,314
Hello.

685
00:30:37,314 --> 00:30:39,850
- Is Jin Joo in her room, by any chance?
- Do you want to talk to Jin Joo? Okay.

686
00:30:39,850 --> 00:30:40,817
Jin Joo.

687
00:30:41,952 --> 00:30:43,587
She's in her room. Jin Joo.

688
00:30:43,587 --> 00:30:44,921
Tell him to wait a moment.

689
00:30:46,123 --> 00:30:47,691
Just a second. She's coming out.

690
00:30:47,691 --> 00:30:48,759
- Wait a bit.
- Okay.

691
00:30:49,559 --> 00:30:50,627
I'll sit here.

692
00:30:53,030 --> 00:30:55,265
Jin Joo, smile, okay?

693
00:30:55,265 --> 00:30:56,133
(Tap)

694
00:30:56,133 --> 00:30:57,467
He's here.

695
00:31:00,237 --> 00:31:02,272
You look more excited.

696
00:31:02,272 --> 00:31:03,407
Where is he?

697
00:31:03,407 --> 00:31:04,875
He's waiting right out front.

698
00:31:04,875 --> 00:31:06,109
Your guy is waiting out front.

699
00:31:06,109 --> 00:31:07,344
Put your shoes on and go.

700
00:31:08,445 --> 00:31:09,513
Jin Joo, you've got this.

701
00:31:09,513 --> 00:31:10,347
Thanks.

702
00:31:11,682 --> 00:31:12,883
She's happy.

703
00:31:13,483 --> 00:31:15,652
Looks like she was waiting.

704
00:31:15,652 --> 00:31:17,788
She looks better now.

705
00:31:19,523 --> 00:31:22,826
(Jin Joo comes outside.)

706
00:31:24,428 --> 00:31:29,599
(The two face each other awkwardly.)

707
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:32,502
I hope Jin Joo doesn't cry again.

708
00:31:32,502 --> 00:31:33,437
No way.

709
00:31:35,372 --> 00:31:41,278
(A quiet place where they can talk alone)

710
00:31:42,846 --> 00:31:44,915
(Reading the room)

711
00:31:49,319 --> 00:31:50,554
What I was thinking was this.

712
00:31:52,255 --> 00:31:53,690
We talked yesterday, right?

713
00:31:54,558 --> 00:31:56,026
About how we should probably
talk more with others.

714
00:31:57,661 --> 00:31:58,428
(Last night)

715
00:31:58,428 --> 00:32:00,330
Did you talk more actively
with your second choice...

716
00:32:00,330 --> 00:32:03,333
and your first choice as well?

717
00:32:04,267 --> 00:32:06,503
I did. I talked enough.

718
00:32:06,503 --> 00:32:08,138
I think you should talk more.

719
00:32:09,406 --> 00:32:11,341
You think so?

720
00:32:11,341 --> 00:32:12,142
Yeah.

721
00:32:12,909 --> 00:32:14,278
So I went with her
without overthinking it,

722
00:32:15,178 --> 00:32:18,181
just thinking,
"Okay, let's talk once more,"

723
00:32:18,982 --> 00:32:21,918
but that ended up
turning into a meal with the mothers too.

724
00:32:23,820 --> 00:32:25,022
What was the question?

725
00:32:25,789 --> 00:32:26,657
The question?

726
00:32:27,057 --> 00:32:28,558
The question before you made your choice.

727
00:32:28,558 --> 00:32:29,393
This morning?

728
00:32:29,793 --> 00:32:31,028
Not word for word,

729
00:32:31,028 --> 00:32:33,830
but "Please stand next to the woman
you want to go on a date with today."

730
00:32:34,698 --> 00:32:35,866
They didn't say
the mothers would be there today.

731
00:32:35,866 --> 00:32:37,901
It wasn't, "Stand next to the person
you want to meet the mother with."

732
00:32:39,403 --> 00:32:42,906
Anyway, I thought that part
probably hurt you more.

733
00:32:43,907 --> 00:32:46,310
It wasn't that getting
zero votes upset me,

734
00:32:46,977 --> 00:32:47,911
it was just...

735
00:32:48,545 --> 00:32:51,748
that you two went to have a meal,
but the mothers also joined.

736
00:32:52,849 --> 00:32:54,651
And on top of that,

737
00:32:54,651 --> 00:32:56,286
your mother had picked her
and her mother had picked you.

738
00:32:57,087 --> 00:32:58,322
That was just...

739
00:33:02,359 --> 00:33:03,260
the worst part.

740
00:33:05,529 --> 00:33:07,931
In the end, I think I'm the problem.

741
00:33:07,931 --> 00:33:09,399
Yeah, that's right.

742
00:33:10,701 --> 00:33:11,768
Is that what you wanted to say?

743
00:33:14,504 --> 00:33:15,606
You went straight for it.

744
00:33:21,478 --> 00:33:24,214
And you answered
every question I asked to confirm that.

745
00:33:26,984 --> 00:33:29,119
But I kept feeling unsure,

746
00:33:29,119 --> 00:33:31,154
wanting to double-check,
wanting more conversation.

747
00:33:32,556 --> 00:33:34,591
So, did you get your confirmation?

748
00:33:34,591 --> 00:33:35,559
I think I did.

749
00:33:38,428 --> 00:33:39,997
That's why I came to talk to you.

750
00:33:40,530 --> 00:33:41,565
That's it, it's settled.

751
00:33:42,165 --> 00:33:43,367
She's smiling.

752
00:33:43,367 --> 00:33:44,701
She's happy again.

753
00:33:45,235 --> 00:33:46,069
Earlier...

754
00:33:46,069 --> 00:33:47,204
Confirmation complete.

755
00:33:47,804 --> 00:33:51,108
I think this made it even clearer.

756
00:33:51,108 --> 00:33:52,943
It wasn't just asking her out on a date.

757
00:33:52,943 --> 00:33:54,678
- Right.
- He really confirmed it.

758
00:33:54,678 --> 00:33:57,281
"Even after going on a date
with someone else and meeting her mother,"

759
00:33:57,281 --> 00:33:58,849
- "in the end, it was you."
- You.

760
00:33:58,849 --> 00:34:01,852
That feels more meaningful.

761
00:34:03,420 --> 00:34:09,593
(The two confirm their feelings
for each other.)

762
00:34:12,729 --> 00:34:13,797
I cried a lot.

763
00:34:14,331 --> 00:34:15,232
You cried?

764
00:34:16,933 --> 00:34:17,801
When?

765
00:34:18,702 --> 00:34:19,603
After you got back?

766
00:34:24,474 --> 00:34:25,309
On the way?

767
00:34:33,884 --> 00:34:34,952
Want to walk a bit?

768
00:34:36,586 --> 00:34:39,323
To that place we said we wanted to go to.
Shall we walk?

769
00:34:41,391 --> 00:34:42,793
This is perfect. They're together.

770
00:34:44,661 --> 00:34:47,931
I should've brought a jacket.

771
00:34:47,931 --> 00:34:48,966
Your coat?

772
00:34:48,966 --> 00:34:49,866
Do you want to wear this?

773
00:34:49,866 --> 00:34:51,168
Yeah, take it off for her.

774
00:34:52,669 --> 00:34:53,837
This is really warm.

775
00:34:53,837 --> 00:34:54,671
It looks warm.

776
00:34:55,072 --> 00:34:56,106
Is it angora?

777
00:34:59,209 --> 00:35:00,410
- Want me to pull your hair out?
- Yeah.

778
00:35:04,448 --> 00:35:05,549
It suits you better.

779
00:35:07,217 --> 00:35:10,287
It must've been tough for you too,
eating with the mothers.

780
00:35:10,287 --> 00:35:11,488
I didn't really talk much.

781
00:35:12,422 --> 00:35:14,958
Did the mothers
start talking about marriage?

782
00:35:16,226 --> 00:35:17,494
Did they tell you guys
to prepare dowries and gifts?

783
00:35:18,962 --> 00:35:20,897
- Did they?
- What are you talking about?

784
00:35:21,932 --> 00:35:23,800
I love that cute jealousy.

785
00:35:24,968 --> 00:35:26,503
No, marriage never came up.

786
00:35:28,639 --> 00:35:29,773
Do we go this way?

787
00:35:29,773 --> 00:35:30,674
Let's try this way.

788
00:35:30,674 --> 00:35:32,109
(They arrive at a café
with jealous Jin Joo.)

789
00:35:32,109 --> 00:35:33,677
Do you want to grab coffee at the café?

790
00:35:33,677 --> 00:35:35,312
I kind of want coffee.

791
00:35:36,747 --> 00:35:38,715
I worried a lot...

792
00:35:38,715 --> 00:35:41,385
about whether I'd get along
with a mother like that.

793
00:35:41,952 --> 00:35:42,986
Let's recharge with some sugar today.

794
00:35:42,986 --> 00:35:49,026
(Min Cheol and Jin Joo
are fully focused on desserts.)

795
00:35:49,860 --> 00:35:51,628
I see.

796
00:35:52,296 --> 00:35:56,433
Then should we just get drinks to go?

797
00:35:56,433 --> 00:35:57,834
That's Min Cheol, right?

798
00:35:58,735 --> 00:35:59,903
Min Cheol and Jin Joo.

799
00:35:59,903 --> 00:36:01,505
Looks like it.

800
00:36:01,505 --> 00:36:06,176
(She spots Min Cheol with Jin Joo.)

801
00:36:06,176 --> 00:36:09,146
I mean, wherever you go,
everything's visible.

802
00:36:09,146 --> 00:36:10,580
They ran into them at the café by chance.

803
00:36:10,580 --> 00:36:14,051
Wasn't that room blocked off earlier?

804
00:36:14,051 --> 00:36:16,353
You can see everything.

805
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:18,221
It's honestly annoying.

806
00:36:20,691 --> 00:36:25,562
I saw him talking to Jin Joo
for the second time.

807
00:36:25,562 --> 00:36:31,702
I thought, "I guess leaving her alone
really bothered him."

808
00:36:31,702 --> 00:36:34,538
And it made me think...

809
00:36:34,938 --> 00:36:38,075
about how I actually feel about Min Cheol.

810
00:36:38,575 --> 00:36:42,179
What about you? I didn't see that coming.

811
00:36:42,746 --> 00:36:44,348
Honestly,

812
00:36:45,882 --> 00:36:48,986
I'm not sure if I like him
because he's a good guy,

813
00:36:48,986 --> 00:36:51,054
or if I like him and want to date him.

814
00:36:53,023 --> 00:36:54,791
I'm not sure.

815
00:36:54,791 --> 00:36:57,327
Then who are you
romantically attracted to?

816
00:36:57,327 --> 00:36:58,362
Hyun Jun.

817
00:36:59,262 --> 00:37:00,831
What?

818
00:37:00,831 --> 00:37:01,898
It was Hyun Jun?

819
00:37:03,867 --> 00:37:05,836
Romantically, I'm drawn to Hyun Jun.

820
00:37:05,836 --> 00:37:08,939
That's interesting. I thought
you'd be more into Min Cheol that way.

821
00:37:08,939 --> 00:37:09,773
That's interesting.

822
00:37:09,773 --> 00:37:11,742
So you like cheerful people?

823
00:37:11,742 --> 00:37:14,745
More than the person.
It's the overall vibe.

824
00:37:14,745 --> 00:37:16,446
I'm drawn to Hyun Jun,

825
00:37:16,446 --> 00:37:20,484
but he's so focused on someone else...

826
00:37:20,484 --> 00:37:21,952
that I can't really approach him.

827
00:37:21,952 --> 00:37:22,786
Why can't you approach him?

828
00:37:22,786 --> 00:37:24,821
It's the last day. Go for it.

829
00:37:24,821 --> 00:37:26,957
Be more proactive.

830
00:37:26,957 --> 00:37:29,660
I'm going to talk to Hyun Jun now.

831
00:37:30,060 --> 00:37:31,328
About what? How he feels?

832
00:37:31,328 --> 00:37:32,362
Yes.

833
00:37:32,362 --> 00:37:33,830
Like a business meeting?

834
00:37:33,830 --> 00:37:36,300
Yeah. How is it?

835
00:37:36,300 --> 00:37:37,401
- Good.
- Good?

836
00:37:38,535 --> 00:37:39,703
Interesting.

837
00:37:40,437 --> 00:37:42,139
- They might actually be compatible.
- Right.

838
00:37:42,139 --> 00:37:43,974
An estrogen-driven man
and a testosterone-driven woman.

839
00:37:43,974 --> 00:37:45,776
So they kind of balance each other out.

840
00:37:45,776 --> 00:37:47,177
Yeah, and he'd live under her thumb.

841
00:37:47,177 --> 00:37:51,515
Honestly, the only person...

842
00:37:51,515 --> 00:37:56,253
who showed even a little curiosity
toward Hyun Jun was Hyun Jin.

843
00:37:57,454 --> 00:37:58,255
First of all...

844
00:37:58,255 --> 00:38:00,290
From what I can see...

845
00:38:00,290 --> 00:38:03,860
Wait. Where's Min Cheol's room
and where's Hyun Jun's room?

846
00:38:03,860 --> 00:38:04,861
They're in the same room.

847
00:38:04,861 --> 00:38:07,264
Really? Then I'll check the situation.

848
00:38:07,264 --> 00:38:08,632
If we call Hyun Jun over...

849
00:38:08,632 --> 00:38:10,200
Where would be a good place
for him to come?

850
00:38:10,200 --> 00:38:12,769
I'll ask him to talk together,
like a consultation.

851
00:38:13,303 --> 00:38:14,304
This side seems better.

852
00:38:14,304 --> 00:38:16,640
Around here, then outside that door.

853
00:38:16,640 --> 00:38:18,809
Could we have him come
to that corner spot?

854
00:38:18,809 --> 00:38:19,743
There?

855
00:38:19,743 --> 00:38:21,612
This is Seung Hak's room.

856
00:38:21,612 --> 00:38:23,814
Hold on, I'll go inside.

857
00:38:24,548 --> 00:38:25,482
Here.

858
00:38:25,482 --> 00:38:27,584
But Seung Hak might be in there.

859
00:38:28,352 --> 00:38:29,286
Seung Hak.

860
00:38:29,286 --> 00:38:29,987
Yes?

861
00:38:29,987 --> 00:38:31,121
Hey.

862
00:38:31,121 --> 00:38:32,856
How many people are there?
Are you alone right now?

863
00:38:33,156 --> 00:38:34,758
- Yes.
- There are two of us.

864
00:38:34,758 --> 00:38:36,593
Hello, ma'am.

865
00:38:36,593 --> 00:38:37,394
I'll step out.

866
00:38:37,394 --> 00:38:39,429
No, it's not like that.

867
00:38:39,429 --> 00:38:40,631
We just wanted to check something.

868
00:38:40,631 --> 00:38:41,832
Check? Seung Hak, check.

869
00:38:41,832 --> 00:38:44,034
No, wait.

870
00:38:44,034 --> 00:38:45,769
You don't have to come out.

871
00:38:45,769 --> 00:38:47,137
I'm going out.

872
00:38:47,137 --> 00:38:49,740
Let's send her to my mother's room.

873
00:38:49,740 --> 00:38:52,242
There's space here too.

874
00:38:52,242 --> 00:38:53,644
My mother is in her room.

875
00:38:53,644 --> 00:38:54,678
Go ahead, talk with him.

876
00:38:55,412 --> 00:38:57,381
(Running)

877
00:38:57,848 --> 00:39:02,052
I want to talk with Hyun Jun.

878
00:39:02,052 --> 00:39:03,020
So she's hoping to borrow this room.

879
00:39:03,020 --> 00:39:04,221
Could I use it for a moment?

880
00:39:04,221 --> 00:39:06,089
Sure.

881
00:39:06,089 --> 00:39:07,691
You can stay too, I guess.

882
00:39:07,691 --> 00:39:09,760
But then he'd hear everything.

883
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:10,827
I'll step out, then.

884
00:39:10,827 --> 00:39:12,429
Okay, I'll take him out with me.

885
00:39:12,429 --> 00:39:13,897
Please tell Hyun Jun to come here.

886
00:39:13,897 --> 00:39:14,765
And...

887
00:39:14,765 --> 00:39:16,900
(The room owner gets ready to leave.)

888
00:39:16,900 --> 00:39:18,001
Yeah, talk.

889
00:39:20,203 --> 00:39:22,306
(Meanwhile, Myo Jin goes to get Hyun Jun.)

890
00:39:22,306 --> 00:39:24,041
- Hello.
- Hey, let's talk for a bit.

891
00:39:25,108 --> 00:39:26,243
Is your mother back?

892
00:39:26,243 --> 00:39:28,578
- Yeah, she's here.
- Hello, ma'am.

893
00:39:28,845 --> 00:39:31,381
Want to go talk in another room?

894
00:39:33,350 --> 00:39:36,019
I don't know, I was just asked.
But anyway, good luck.

895
00:39:36,019 --> 00:39:36,687
Asked to get me?

896
00:39:37,254 --> 00:39:38,822
Someone asked. Hello.

897
00:39:38,822 --> 00:39:39,690
Hi.

898
00:39:39,957 --> 00:39:41,758
Okay, now you step out, Seung Hak.

899
00:39:41,758 --> 00:39:43,093
I'll leave once they come in.

900
00:39:43,093 --> 00:39:44,027
They're here.

901
00:39:44,728 --> 00:39:47,731
- Nice to meet you.
- How about we talk for a bit?

902
00:39:47,731 --> 00:39:48,999
- Where's Seung Hak?
- Here.

903
00:39:48,999 --> 00:39:50,167
You come out.

904
00:39:50,167 --> 00:39:51,134
- What?
- Hi.

905
00:39:51,134 --> 00:39:52,369
You scared me.

906
00:39:52,369 --> 00:39:53,470
It's me.

907
00:39:53,470 --> 00:39:54,738
Did you have a good time?

908
00:39:54,738 --> 00:39:56,373
It's not Seung Hak. It's me.

909
00:39:56,373 --> 00:39:58,575
I see. I was wondering why Seung Hak
would want a one-on-one with me.

910
00:39:58,575 --> 00:39:59,409
Okay, bye.

911
00:39:59,409 --> 00:40:00,811
(Shy)

912
00:40:01,411 --> 00:40:02,512
Hi.

913
00:40:03,313 --> 00:40:04,147
Did you have a good time?

914
00:40:04,147 --> 00:40:05,882
I'm curious
what they're going to talk about.

915
00:40:05,882 --> 00:40:06,817
Did you have a good time?

916
00:40:08,919 --> 00:40:11,555
You should've come out on your own.

917
00:40:13,290 --> 00:40:14,791
- Let's go.
- How was the meal earlier?

918
00:40:14,791 --> 00:40:16,760
The meal?
I seriously thought I was going to choke.

919
00:40:16,760 --> 00:40:17,694
Hello.

920
00:40:17,694 --> 00:40:19,529
(Se Hoon)

921
00:40:19,529 --> 00:40:20,931
Are the mothers together?

922
00:40:20,931 --> 00:40:22,633
Yeah, his mother and my mother.

923
00:40:22,633 --> 00:40:24,835
Okay. Let's talk later.

924
00:40:24,835 --> 00:40:25,836
Okay.

925
00:40:25,836 --> 00:40:26,837
Anyway...

926
00:40:27,537 --> 00:40:29,606
To be honest,

927
00:40:29,606 --> 00:40:31,074
you know I have feelings for you.

928
00:40:34,444 --> 00:40:36,480
She's so direct.

929
00:40:37,981 --> 00:40:39,716
(A blunt confession from Hyun Jin)

930
00:40:39,716 --> 00:40:40,851
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

931
00:40:41,318 --> 00:40:42,619
But...

932
00:40:42,986 --> 00:40:45,856
What I find strange is...
Why?

933
00:40:45,856 --> 00:40:47,057
I mean, this also feels strange.

934
00:40:47,057 --> 00:40:48,125
I didn't mean to ask "why."

935
00:40:49,226 --> 00:40:51,428
Are you asking why I like you?

936
00:40:51,428 --> 00:40:53,163
No, that's not it.

937
00:40:53,163 --> 00:40:54,331
It's just that...

938
00:40:54,931 --> 00:40:56,600
Stop covering your eyes.

939
00:40:56,600 --> 00:40:57,668
Don't do weird stuff.

940
00:40:58,135 --> 00:40:59,436
Honestly...

941
00:41:00,103 --> 00:41:01,571
I'm just a little shy.

942
00:41:01,571 --> 00:41:05,175
Didn't you talk with Min Cheol
for a long time last night?

943
00:41:05,175 --> 00:41:07,144
- Yeah, we talked.
- Right?

944
00:41:07,144 --> 00:41:09,680
But my own feelings matter too,
that's why.

945
00:41:10,380 --> 00:41:11,248
I see.

946
00:41:12,149 --> 00:41:13,116
Then,

947
00:41:13,750 --> 00:41:15,953
does that mean I'm number one,
not Min Cheol?

948
00:41:17,087 --> 00:41:18,322
I mean, my first and second picks
are really close.

949
00:41:18,322 --> 00:41:19,923
They're not far apart.

950
00:41:19,923 --> 00:41:21,258
They're pretty even?

951
00:41:21,258 --> 00:41:23,794
But since you still need to talk
before this shoot is over...

952
00:41:23,794 --> 00:41:25,796
Yes, and I talked
with Min Cheol yesterday.

953
00:41:25,796 --> 00:41:27,097
And again today.

954
00:41:27,097 --> 00:41:30,667
And I realized...

955
00:41:30,667 --> 00:41:33,637
I hadn't really had
a serious talk with you.

956
00:41:33,637 --> 00:41:35,372
Right, we were always just joking around.

957
00:41:35,372 --> 00:41:37,274
And honestly, I was too shy.

958
00:41:37,708 --> 00:41:39,343
Really? What's there to be shy about?

959
00:41:40,110 --> 00:41:41,578
Everything.

960
00:41:41,578 --> 00:41:43,313
Yeah?

961
00:41:43,313 --> 00:41:44,414
I don't know.

962
00:41:44,414 --> 00:41:46,583
I'm someone
who's never really known shyness.

963
00:41:46,583 --> 00:41:47,951
You seem like the type
who'd be the most shy.

964
00:41:49,119 --> 00:41:51,555
Anyway, that's why I came.

965
00:41:52,422 --> 00:41:55,192
Even though you knew how I felt...

966
00:41:55,192 --> 00:41:56,660
I still went to someone else.

967
00:41:56,660 --> 00:41:58,395
Yeah, but you knew already.

968
00:41:58,895 --> 00:42:01,131
Before I regretted it,
I wanted to talk to you.

969
00:42:01,131 --> 00:42:03,667
You wanted to do everything you could,
all the way to the end?

970
00:42:04,234 --> 00:42:07,738
Because tomorrow is decision day.

971
00:42:07,738 --> 00:42:10,274
Yeah, full-on testosterone-driven mode.

972
00:42:10,274 --> 00:42:11,708
You're definitely
a testosterone-driven lady.

973
00:42:12,175 --> 00:42:13,977
"I'm going all in, no regrets."

974
00:42:13,977 --> 00:42:15,112
That's honestly really cool.

975
00:42:15,112 --> 00:42:15,979
No, it's not cool.

976
00:42:15,979 --> 00:42:17,981
You're seriously cool.

977
00:42:17,981 --> 00:42:20,450
You really are.

978
00:42:20,450 --> 00:42:23,553
Anyway, I didn't want to have regrets.

979
00:42:23,553 --> 00:42:25,756
I'm really grateful.

980
00:42:25,756 --> 00:42:26,790
But I kept...

981
00:42:26,790 --> 00:42:30,027
being conscious of Tae In.

982
00:42:30,027 --> 00:42:31,094
That's how it felt.

983
00:42:31,094 --> 00:42:32,062
So...

984
00:42:32,062 --> 00:42:33,964
sometimes I think if things had gone
differently with you first,

985
00:42:33,964 --> 00:42:36,066
maybe Tae In wouldn't have stayed
on my mind so much.

986
00:42:36,066 --> 00:42:37,434
The other way around?

987
00:42:37,434 --> 00:42:38,802
But because Tae In came first...

988
00:42:38,802 --> 00:42:39,636
Right.

989
00:42:39,636 --> 00:42:44,608
If we get another chance,
let's talk more then.

990
00:42:44,608 --> 00:42:45,642
Yeah.

991
00:42:45,642 --> 00:42:46,443
Just...

992
00:42:46,443 --> 00:42:47,844
(Good)

993
00:42:47,844 --> 00:42:48,578
Okay.

994
00:42:49,846 --> 00:42:52,649
He explained it...

995
00:42:52,649 --> 00:42:54,251
as "maybe it was a timing issue,"

996
00:42:54,251 --> 00:42:57,187
and I honestly understood that.

997
00:42:57,187 --> 00:43:00,057
If anything, my heart felt lighter.

998
00:43:01,124 --> 00:43:04,294
What I find really unfortunate
about Hyun Jun is this.

999
00:43:04,294 --> 00:43:05,562
If it were me,

1000
00:43:05,562 --> 00:43:07,965
at this timing, I would've boldly...

1001
00:43:08,398 --> 00:43:10,634
turned toward Hyun Jin at least a little.

1002
00:43:10,634 --> 00:43:12,869
He already met her mother too.

1003
00:43:12,869 --> 00:43:14,871
Hyun Jin is in an awkward position
right now too.

1004
00:43:14,871 --> 00:43:15,906
Right.

1005
00:43:15,906 --> 00:43:18,875
This was really the timing to go that way,

1006
00:43:18,875 --> 00:43:20,177
but he didn't.

1007
00:43:21,111 --> 00:43:25,115
That situation felt too stiff.

1008
00:43:25,115 --> 00:43:25,882
Yeah.

1009
00:43:26,550 --> 00:43:27,551
And on top of that,

1010
00:43:27,551 --> 00:43:32,956
being together with Se Hoon
and his mother instead of one-on-one...

1011
00:43:32,956 --> 00:43:36,093
suddenly felt really draining.

1012
00:43:36,093 --> 00:43:38,528
Right? I was tired too.

1013
00:43:38,528 --> 00:43:41,565
But I think seeing my mother recharged me.

1014
00:43:41,565 --> 00:43:42,699
Just now? Seeing your mother?

1015
00:43:42,699 --> 00:43:45,602
And having all the mothers together
made me really happy.

1016
00:43:45,602 --> 00:43:46,937
So I felt really good.

1017
00:43:49,139 --> 00:43:50,841
See you later. Get some rest.

1018
00:43:50,841 --> 00:43:52,109
Get some sleep.

1019
00:43:52,109 --> 00:43:53,210
Where are you going?

1020
00:43:53,410 --> 00:43:54,778
- I'm heading this way.
- Really?

1021
00:43:54,778 --> 00:43:57,948
Then on your way, call Se Hoon over.
That'd be better.

1022
00:43:58,849 --> 00:44:04,788
(Cry)

1023
00:44:06,290 --> 00:44:09,459
This is kind of weird though, right?

1024
00:44:10,260 --> 00:44:12,329
Well, what can you do?
You were chosen by two people.

1025
00:44:12,329 --> 00:44:13,830
But still...

1026
00:44:14,531 --> 00:44:15,198
It's fine.

1027
00:44:15,198 --> 00:44:16,700
- Se Hoon.
- I'm so torn.

1028
00:44:18,001 --> 00:44:19,336
(His mother gets up instead of him.)

1029
00:44:19,336 --> 00:44:20,237
Where's Se Hoon?

1030
00:44:21,805 --> 00:44:23,273
Everything feels...

1031
00:44:23,273 --> 00:44:26,443
so strange now that the mothers are here.

1032
00:44:26,443 --> 00:44:27,577
It's really not easy, right?

1033
00:44:27,577 --> 00:44:28,745
Yeah, it's really not easy.

1034
00:44:28,745 --> 00:44:30,247
It's okay.

1035
00:44:30,247 --> 00:44:32,049
Just pretend we're not here.

1036
00:44:32,049 --> 00:44:34,718
Then we can go out again.

1037
00:44:34,718 --> 00:44:35,686
Myo Jin.

1038
00:44:35,686 --> 00:44:38,322
You're all right there.
How can we pretend you're not here?

1039
00:44:38,322 --> 00:44:40,757
Just think of us as ghosts.

1040
00:44:40,757 --> 00:44:43,694
Tell the producers to send us out again.

1041
00:44:43,694 --> 00:44:44,761
Really?

1042
00:44:44,761 --> 00:44:46,063
Then we'll just go out again.

1043
00:44:46,730 --> 00:44:49,299
(Fortunately, the son and daughter leave.)

1044
00:44:49,633 --> 00:44:51,835
Out of everyone,
why are those two together?

1045
00:44:52,402 --> 00:44:53,704
We'll be back.

1046
00:44:54,104 --> 00:44:55,272
Are you leaving with Se Jin?

1047
00:44:55,272 --> 00:44:56,873
I mean, Se Hoon?

1048
00:44:57,541 --> 00:44:59,376
We already had a talk.

1049
00:45:00,510 --> 00:45:01,411
(Turn)

1050
00:45:01,812 --> 00:45:03,046
It was just a question.

1051
00:45:08,051 --> 00:45:11,922
I'm really curious how it was
with the other mothers.

1052
00:45:11,922 --> 00:45:12,856
Same.

1053
00:45:13,156 --> 00:45:15,292
The mothers looked super nervous.

1054
00:45:15,292 --> 00:45:16,026
Exactly.

1055
00:45:16,026 --> 00:45:18,395
They kept breaking into a sweat.

1056
00:45:21,164 --> 00:45:24,735
If your mother told you
not to see someone, would you stop?

1057
00:45:25,435 --> 00:45:28,138
No, I really wouldn't care about that.

1058
00:45:30,407 --> 00:45:32,276
I do what I want.

1059
00:45:32,542 --> 00:45:33,577
But who knows?

1060
00:45:33,577 --> 00:45:38,181
If my mother said, "This person
really isn't marriage material"...

1061
00:45:38,181 --> 00:45:40,250
- And had a reasonable...
- Yeah.

1062
00:45:40,851 --> 00:45:42,552
and logical reason, then maybe.

1063
00:45:42,552 --> 00:45:44,421
But my mother...

1064
00:45:44,421 --> 00:45:47,224
mostly trusts my choices.

1065
00:45:47,224 --> 00:45:49,693
She knows I'll figure things out
on my own.

1066
00:45:50,827 --> 00:45:51,895
That's how she is.

1067
00:45:54,564 --> 00:45:56,033
You're confused, aren't you?

1068
00:45:56,033 --> 00:45:57,401
- What?
- Are you confused?

1069
00:46:01,571 --> 00:46:03,407
Honestly, I think I am.

1070
00:46:03,407 --> 00:46:04,141
Right?

1071
00:46:04,141 --> 00:46:04,908
Yeah.

1072
00:46:05,375 --> 00:46:06,610
Still confused?

1073
00:46:07,044 --> 00:46:08,845
Feels like he doesn't
really need to be anymore.

1074
00:46:13,884 --> 00:46:15,886
But right now, this feels so good.

1075
00:46:16,687 --> 00:46:17,788
So stay with me just a little longer.

1076
00:46:41,778 --> 00:46:43,080
Well...

1077
00:46:44,481 --> 00:46:47,584
What is this?

1078
00:46:47,584 --> 00:46:49,052
What is going on?

1079
00:46:50,020 --> 00:46:51,622
I was wondering.

1080
00:46:51,622 --> 00:46:54,324
It felt really good,

1081
00:46:55,292 --> 00:46:56,560
but I wasn't quite sure...

1082
00:46:57,327 --> 00:46:58,729
and it was strange.

1083
00:46:58,729 --> 00:47:00,897
It was a mix...

1084
00:47:00,897 --> 00:47:03,600
of a lot of emotions and thoughts.

1085
00:47:04,768 --> 00:47:05,902
"What is this?"

1086
00:47:06,570 --> 00:47:08,872
That's how it felt the whole time.

1087
00:47:08,872 --> 00:47:10,741
Complicated, subtle emotions.

1088
00:47:12,242 --> 00:47:13,010
That's heart-fluttering.

1089
00:47:13,010 --> 00:47:15,012
Those kinds of lines
make your heart flutter.

1090
00:47:16,280 --> 00:47:18,615
But now,

1091
00:47:18,615 --> 00:47:20,517
she kind of wants to hear "I choose you."

1092
00:47:20,517 --> 00:47:21,585
Right. She wants to hear that now.

1093
00:47:21,585 --> 00:47:22,986
- But he won't say it.
- He keeps saying he's confused.

1094
00:47:22,986 --> 00:47:25,122
He won't say it, no matter what.

1095
00:47:25,689 --> 00:47:26,923
That's how you drive people crazy.

1096
00:47:28,492 --> 00:47:32,195
Later, when you like someone, Yo Han,

1097
00:47:32,195 --> 00:47:33,063
Yes.

1098
00:47:34,064 --> 00:47:35,666
tell her quickly.

1099
00:47:36,400 --> 00:47:38,402
Yeah. Don't keep saying you're confused.

1100
00:47:38,402 --> 00:47:40,170
Don't go, "I'm so confused."

1101
00:47:40,170 --> 00:47:41,238
"I'm confused."

1102
00:47:41,238 --> 00:47:42,406
Just be honest.

1103
00:47:42,406 --> 00:47:45,142
People like Yo Han need clarity fast.

1104
00:47:45,142 --> 00:47:46,043
Got it.

1105
00:47:48,712 --> 00:47:52,382
(Myo Jin returns
after talking with Se Hoon.)

1106
00:47:52,849 --> 00:47:54,551
I think...

1107
00:47:55,252 --> 00:47:58,689
I'm definitely more drawn to Se Hoon,

1108
00:47:58,989 --> 00:48:03,460
and he's closer to the type
I usually like.

1109
00:48:03,460 --> 00:48:08,565
But after talking,
the way he treats his mother...

1110
00:48:08,565 --> 00:48:11,335
felt a bit stiff.

1111
00:48:11,335 --> 00:48:12,703
Was he stiff with his mother?

1112
00:48:12,703 --> 00:48:15,472
It seemed so with his mother.

1113
00:48:15,472 --> 00:48:16,907
A bit.

1114
00:48:17,608 --> 00:48:22,512
You're not that close
with your mother usually, right?

1115
00:48:22,946 --> 00:48:24,114
It shows, doesn't it?

1116
00:48:24,114 --> 00:48:27,250
Not exactly. But once you said it,
I could see it clearly.

1117
00:48:28,018 --> 00:48:32,255
If I say one thing wrong,
my mother just bursts.

1118
00:48:32,255 --> 00:48:33,523
She gets really hurt.

1119
00:48:33,523 --> 00:48:35,993
You were pretty intense.

1120
00:48:36,793 --> 00:48:40,664
If you talk to her with that look,
of course she'd cry.

1121
00:48:43,400 --> 00:48:49,406
People like that end up treating
their wives the same way after marriage.

1122
00:48:49,406 --> 00:48:50,040
Right.

1123
00:48:50,874 --> 00:48:51,508
(Sigh...)

1124
00:48:51,508 --> 00:48:53,210
I don't know.

1125
00:48:53,210 --> 00:48:58,115
No one is ever 100 percent my ideal type.

1126
00:48:58,115 --> 00:49:00,183
You know what I mean?

1127
00:49:00,550 --> 00:49:02,853
I'm attracted,

1128
00:49:06,223 --> 00:49:07,190
but it's hard.

1129
00:49:07,858 --> 00:49:08,959
- Right.
- Yeah.

1130
00:49:08,959 --> 00:49:10,494
The more you go through this,
the harder it gets.

1131
00:49:10,494 --> 00:49:11,295
Yeah.

1132
00:49:13,030 --> 00:49:15,399
Han Gyeol, do you have a moment?

1133
00:49:15,399 --> 00:49:16,166
Yeah.

1134
00:49:16,767 --> 00:49:19,236
It's easier to come out this way.

1135
00:49:19,236 --> 00:49:22,105
(He rushes to the window
at Eun Na Rae's call.)

1136
00:49:22,105 --> 00:49:23,507
- It's a small door.
- That's so cute.

1137
00:49:25,442 --> 00:49:26,543
(Glance)

1138
00:49:26,543 --> 00:49:27,344
Hey.

1139
00:49:27,344 --> 00:49:28,178
Where should we go?

1140
00:49:28,178 --> 00:49:29,913
Here. Give it to your mother.

1141
00:49:29,913 --> 00:49:31,214
My mother? Why?

1142
00:49:31,214 --> 00:49:33,583
And this too.

1143
00:49:33,583 --> 00:49:34,551
- For me?
- Yeah.

1144
00:49:34,985 --> 00:49:38,488
I think one box will be enough.

1145
00:49:39,256 --> 00:49:40,891
(A handwritten letter as well)

1146
00:49:40,891 --> 00:49:41,992
Even a letter.

1147
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:44,494
For you and your mother.

1148
00:49:44,494 --> 00:49:48,432
There's nothing big in it, but earlier,

1149
00:49:48,432 --> 00:49:49,433
during that meal...

1150
00:49:51,435 --> 00:49:54,338
That moment just kept bothering me.

1151
00:49:54,338 --> 00:49:55,072
What bothered you?

1152
00:49:55,072 --> 00:49:57,641
I don't know.
It was just awkward and uncomfortable.

1153
00:49:57,641 --> 00:49:59,042
What bothered you?

1154
00:49:59,042 --> 00:50:00,143
What exactly?

1155
00:50:00,143 --> 00:50:04,214
It felt like I should've said more,

1156
00:50:04,214 --> 00:50:05,916
but the words just wouldn't come.

1157
00:50:05,916 --> 00:50:07,784
I didn't know what to say.

1158
00:50:07,784 --> 00:50:09,052
Same here.

1159
00:50:09,886 --> 00:50:10,854
How sweet of you.

1160
00:50:13,023 --> 00:50:14,491
Let's talk again later tonight.

1161
00:50:15,459 --> 00:50:16,293
See you later.

1162
00:50:16,293 --> 00:50:17,060
Okay.

1163
00:50:19,196 --> 00:50:20,230
- Mom.
- Yeah?

1164
00:50:20,664 --> 00:50:25,736
Eun Na Rae bought us bread.

1165
00:50:25,736 --> 00:50:26,937
She bought it for us?

1166
00:50:26,937 --> 00:50:28,405
She went out and got it?

1167
00:50:28,739 --> 00:50:32,809
I think so. Maybe what happened earlier
was still on her mind.

1168
00:50:32,809 --> 00:50:34,678
Why? What was she hung up on?

1169
00:50:37,814 --> 00:50:42,619
(Eun Na Rae's thoughtful
handwritten letter)

1170
00:50:43,020 --> 00:50:44,288
Isn't it cute?

1171
00:50:44,288 --> 00:50:45,155
Yeah.

1172
00:50:45,589 --> 00:50:47,124
- Right?
- Yeah.

1173
00:50:48,091 --> 00:50:49,526
She asked me to pass it on to you, Mom.

1174
00:50:49,526 --> 00:50:50,560
Okay.

1175
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:52,963
(As evening mealtime arrives)

1176
00:51:00,203 --> 00:51:02,205
What should we do?

1177
00:51:02,205 --> 00:51:04,141
(This space is open only for
filming purposes with permission.)

1178
00:51:04,341 --> 00:51:05,342
Look at you.

1179
00:51:05,976 --> 00:51:08,078
- You went to freshen up a bit.
- Me?

1180
00:51:08,078 --> 00:51:09,947
You should tie your hair up
if you're cooking.

1181
00:51:11,949 --> 00:51:12,749
Hello, ma'am.

1182
00:51:12,749 --> 00:51:13,750
Hello.

1183
00:51:18,155 --> 00:51:19,556
Mom, grill it.

1184
00:51:19,556 --> 00:51:21,391
"Mom, grill it?" I knew you'd say that.

1185
00:51:21,391 --> 00:51:22,759
It just looked like
you didn't have anything to do.

1186
00:51:23,527 --> 00:51:24,461
Ma'am, I'll do it.

1187
00:51:24,461 --> 00:51:25,929
No, it's okay, I'll do it.

1188
00:51:25,929 --> 00:51:27,331
No, I'll do it.

1189
00:51:27,331 --> 00:51:29,833
It'll look like I dumped it on you
after Jin Joo handed it to me.

1190
00:51:29,833 --> 00:51:31,501
No, it's fine.

1191
00:51:31,501 --> 00:51:32,936
Just relax. I'll keep grilling the meat.

1192
00:51:32,936 --> 00:51:34,404
Then I'll cut the garlic in half.

1193
00:51:34,404 --> 00:51:35,339
Thank you.

1194
00:51:36,373 --> 00:51:37,407
(Meanwhile,
Jin Joo, who "passed off" the meat)

1195
00:51:37,407 --> 00:51:38,809
I'll wash these with you.

1196
00:51:40,010 --> 00:51:41,078
Hello.

1197
00:51:41,078 --> 00:51:42,245
(She goes to help Min Cheol's mother.)

1198
00:51:42,245 --> 00:51:43,280
Thank you.

1199
00:51:45,382 --> 00:51:46,683
Aren't your hands cold?

1200
00:51:46,683 --> 00:51:47,517
Hello.

1201
00:51:47,517 --> 00:51:49,620
The water isn't cold,

1202
00:51:49,620 --> 00:51:50,787
so I'm okay.

1203
00:51:50,787 --> 00:51:52,556
(Seung Hak's mother
moves next to Myo Jin.)

1204
00:51:53,457 --> 00:51:54,725
Everyone looks so happy.

1205
00:51:56,960 --> 00:51:57,961
Thank you for the gift

1206
00:51:59,896 --> 00:52:01,064
Enjoy your bread.

1207
00:52:03,834 --> 00:52:06,203
(Grin)

1208
00:52:06,670 --> 00:52:08,705
I think we can bring all of this out.

1209
00:52:08,705 --> 00:52:09,906
It turned into something
like spicy pork stir-fry.

1210
00:52:10,540 --> 00:52:11,341
Looks delicious.

1211
00:52:11,842 --> 00:52:14,211
It looks so good, nice, and hot.

1212
00:52:15,045 --> 00:52:16,480
Give me the perilla leaves, ma'am.

1213
00:52:16,480 --> 00:52:17,914
- I've got nothing in my hands.
- Okay.

1214
00:52:17,914 --> 00:52:19,516
- It's heavy.
- It's not.

1215
00:52:19,516 --> 00:52:21,418
It's heavy. You'll strain your wrist.

1216
00:52:22,185 --> 00:52:23,553
- It is heavy.
- Let's go.

1217
00:52:28,258 --> 00:52:31,261
(The final dinner, all together)

1218
00:52:31,261 --> 00:52:33,063
It's already the last evening.

1219
00:52:36,199 --> 00:52:37,467
Enjoy your meal.

1220
00:52:37,467 --> 00:52:38,869
Thank you.

1221
00:52:38,869 --> 00:52:40,904
Please enjoy.

1222
00:52:40,904 --> 00:52:41,872
I'll try this.

1223
00:52:41,872 --> 00:52:42,739
Eat up.

1224
00:52:43,640 --> 00:52:45,943
I hardly ever get to eat food
my son makes.

1225
00:52:46,476 --> 00:52:48,478
Because he's always out and about.

1226
00:52:48,478 --> 00:52:49,680
So I only get it at times like this.

1227
00:52:51,281 --> 00:52:52,916
I'll try opening it with this.

1228
00:52:55,218 --> 00:52:55,686
(Pop)

1229
00:52:56,787 --> 00:52:57,854
Nice.

1230
00:52:57,854 --> 00:52:59,423
My goodness.

1231
00:52:59,690 --> 00:53:02,059
It's supposed to go "Pop!"
when you do it right.

1232
00:53:03,493 --> 00:53:05,529
(Another bottle)

1233
00:53:05,529 --> 00:53:07,731
(Tries another bottle in disappointment)

1234
00:53:07,731 --> 00:53:08,098
(Pop)

1235
00:53:08,565 --> 00:53:10,701
Yes.

1236
00:53:10,701 --> 00:53:13,570
I thought only my husband
did things like that.

1237
00:53:13,570 --> 00:53:15,505
I practiced this for over a year.

1238
00:53:16,173 --> 00:53:19,876
That's amazing.

1239
00:53:20,277 --> 00:53:23,480
- She opened it with a spoon.
- Really?

1240
00:53:23,480 --> 00:53:26,416
Watch Seung Hak's mother.

1241
00:53:26,850 --> 00:53:28,018
Attention.

1242
00:53:28,018 --> 00:53:29,519
Watch.

1243
00:53:29,519 --> 00:53:31,355
- Watch.
- She's opening it.

1244
00:53:31,355 --> 00:53:33,223
Watch.

1245
00:53:33,223 --> 00:53:33,991
(Pop)

1246
00:53:34,992 --> 00:53:36,827
(Proud)

1247
00:53:36,827 --> 00:53:38,829
- The best.
- That's awesome.

1248
00:53:38,829 --> 00:53:40,430
(Good job, Mom)

1249
00:53:41,331 --> 00:53:43,100
It was great being with you all.

1250
00:53:46,370 --> 00:53:47,638
This is seriously so refreshing.

1251
00:53:47,638 --> 00:53:48,905
Right? It's got that sharp bite.

1252
00:53:49,873 --> 00:53:52,175
How does it go this well with pork belly?

1253
00:53:52,175 --> 00:53:53,176
It pairs so well with food.

1254
00:53:53,176 --> 00:53:54,444
This is insane.

1255
00:53:56,346 --> 00:53:58,148
It's cold.

1256
00:54:03,654 --> 00:54:08,659
(Min Cheol hands Jin Joo
his padded jacket.)

1257
00:54:09,926 --> 00:54:11,662
This is so thick.

1258
00:54:11,662 --> 00:54:12,629
That's warm.

1259
00:54:13,563 --> 00:54:15,332
This is so thick.

1260
00:54:15,332 --> 00:54:16,166
That's warm.

1261
00:54:17,734 --> 00:54:18,769
Hyun Jin's mother...

1262
00:54:18,769 --> 00:54:19,870
(Awkward laugh)

1263
00:54:19,870 --> 00:54:21,171
(Awkward laugh)

1264
00:54:21,171 --> 00:54:22,940
No.

1265
00:54:23,140 --> 00:54:25,442
He went on a lunch date with Hyun Jin,

1266
00:54:25,442 --> 00:54:28,745
then went on another date
with someone else in the evening,

1267
00:54:29,112 --> 00:54:32,716
and now he's even
taking his jacket off for her.

1268
00:54:32,716 --> 00:54:36,453
I honestly don't get what's in his head.

1269
00:54:37,187 --> 00:54:38,555
That feels pretty lousy.

1270
00:54:40,023 --> 00:54:43,126
(Puts on her own jacket, displeased)

1271
00:54:43,293 --> 00:54:46,063
- Pour a drink for your future son-in-law.
- You've got to make a good impression.

1272
00:54:46,063 --> 00:54:48,832
Go pour a drink for the man.

1273
00:54:49,666 --> 00:54:51,935
Everyone already knows.

1274
00:54:51,935 --> 00:54:55,372
It's already way too obvious,
so I don't even need to.

1275
00:54:55,372 --> 00:54:56,506
Still, go pour him a drink.

1276
00:54:56,506 --> 00:54:59,276
- I can't.
- Just try.

1277
00:54:59,276 --> 00:55:01,545
I have a conscience. I don't think I can.

1278
00:55:01,545 --> 00:55:03,046
A conscience?

1279
00:55:03,046 --> 00:55:04,081
It's embarrassing.

1280
00:55:04,081 --> 00:55:05,582
I should do it.

1281
00:55:05,582 --> 00:55:06,483
Where are you going?

1282
00:55:07,284 --> 00:55:09,286
(Heads somewhere with resolve)

1283
00:55:09,286 --> 00:55:10,287
Min Cheol.

1284
00:55:10,604 --> 00:55:12,239
Here, have a drink.

1285
00:55:12,239 --> 00:55:13,741
Her mother...

1286
00:55:14,675 --> 00:55:16,143
Jin Joo's mother.

1287
00:55:16,143 --> 00:55:17,444
She...

1288
00:55:17,845 --> 00:55:20,948
Min Cheol, I'll pour you a drink.

1289
00:55:20,948 --> 00:55:22,716
I'll pour you a drink.

1290
00:55:22,716 --> 00:55:23,751
Thank you, ma'am.

1291
00:55:23,751 --> 00:55:24,718
(Stands up abruptly)

1292
00:55:25,719 --> 00:55:28,055
My goodness.

1293
00:55:28,055 --> 00:55:29,523
Looks like he's been chosen.

1294
00:55:31,358 --> 00:55:34,295
(Jin Joo's mother gathers courage
and approaches Min Cheol.)

1295
00:55:34,295 --> 00:55:36,263
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

1296
00:55:37,698 --> 00:55:38,799
I worked up the courage.

1297
00:55:38,799 --> 00:55:39,667
Thank you, ma'am.

1298
00:55:41,735 --> 00:55:43,937
She's honestly so cool.

1299
00:55:43,937 --> 00:55:45,906
Young moms really are different.

1300
00:55:46,740 --> 00:55:48,509
(I liked that.)

1301
00:55:49,209 --> 00:55:50,411
Thank you, ma'am.

1302
00:55:50,411 --> 00:55:53,480
Chug it.

1303
00:55:56,483 --> 00:55:57,685
That's it.

1304
00:55:57,685 --> 00:55:59,253
You've got to finish it
shake it over your head.

1305
00:55:59,620 --> 00:56:01,555
That's awesome.

1306
00:56:01,555 --> 00:56:03,157
So cool.

1307
00:56:03,891 --> 00:56:06,293
I'm happy because Jin Joo's smiling.

1308
00:56:06,293 --> 00:56:07,594
What a relief...

1309
00:56:08,295 --> 00:56:09,563
that Jin Joo can smile.

1310
00:56:10,731 --> 00:56:13,867
Jin Joo also told me this.

1311
00:56:13,867 --> 00:56:16,170
(During lunch that day)

1312
00:56:16,170 --> 00:56:17,538
Mom, you should go over to Min Cheol.

1313
00:56:19,006 --> 00:56:20,441
What? Why would I?

1314
00:56:21,442 --> 00:56:22,876
Give him a little nudge.

1315
00:56:22,876 --> 00:56:24,144
How am I supposed to nudge him?

1316
00:56:25,179 --> 00:56:26,413
Mom, you're popular.

1317
00:56:27,514 --> 00:56:30,751
To show my support,
I gathered my courage...

1318
00:56:32,052 --> 00:56:34,254
and poured Min Cheol a drink.

1319
00:56:34,254 --> 00:56:35,723
(The mother approaches Min Cheol
at her daughter's request.)

1320
00:56:35,723 --> 00:56:39,760
I wanted to be a mother
who could help Jin Joo.

1321
00:56:39,760 --> 00:56:41,662
Someone Jin Joo can like,

1322
00:56:41,662 --> 00:56:43,397
and someone who will like Jin Joo.

1323
00:56:43,897 --> 00:56:46,834
I kept thinking he might be that person.

1324
00:56:47,501 --> 00:56:50,671
I'm so grateful to my mother,

1325
00:56:51,305 --> 00:56:54,074
and also to Min Cheol
for taking it so kindly.

1326
00:56:54,775 --> 00:56:55,976
Right.

1327
00:56:55,976 --> 00:56:57,645
They're writing a drama.

1328
00:56:58,412 --> 00:57:00,948
Jin Joo's mother stepped forward first.

1329
00:57:00,948 --> 00:57:02,916
- Even though that's not really her style.
- No, it isn't.

1330
00:57:02,916 --> 00:57:03,751
But just now...

1331
00:57:03,751 --> 00:57:04,818
She's showing how she feels.

1332
00:57:04,818 --> 00:57:08,989
She stepped up for her daughter.

1333
00:57:08,989 --> 00:57:09,757
For her child.

1334
00:57:09,757 --> 00:57:11,125
She went all in to seal the deal.

1335
00:57:11,125 --> 00:57:13,694
That's how mothers feel.

1336
00:57:15,029 --> 00:57:16,163
Thank you, ma'am.

1337
00:57:17,031 --> 00:57:18,032
That's awesome.

1338
00:57:18,032 --> 00:57:19,833
She's really amazing.

1339
00:57:19,833 --> 00:57:20,834
Seriously.

1340
00:57:20,834 --> 00:57:22,036
That was impactful.

1341
00:57:24,071 --> 00:57:26,907
(After the final dinner ends)

1342
00:57:27,608 --> 00:57:30,277
Earlier, when we went to dinner,

1343
00:57:31,278 --> 00:57:33,681
Hyun Jin didn't look at me at first.

1344
00:57:33,681 --> 00:57:34,448
Really?

1345
00:57:34,448 --> 00:57:37,484
The moment I walked in, I noticed her.

1346
00:57:37,484 --> 00:57:39,253
But she couldn't look at me.

1347
00:57:40,721 --> 00:57:43,691
Later, when I kept looking,

1348
00:57:43,691 --> 00:57:46,327
she finally smiled at me.

1349
00:57:47,861 --> 00:57:49,697
- She must've felt something too.
- Right.

1350
00:57:51,298 --> 00:57:54,268
I guess I can't help
being the bad guy to someone.

1351
00:57:54,268 --> 00:57:55,169
Yeah.

1352
00:57:56,470 --> 00:57:57,338
Jin Joo's here.

1353
00:57:58,973 --> 00:57:59,907
How cute.

1354
00:58:00,941 --> 00:58:03,410
(Jin Joo comes to return Min Cheol's hat.)

1355
00:58:04,011 --> 00:58:04,912
Hello.

1356
00:58:04,912 --> 00:58:07,047
Both of the jackets
Jin Joo's holding are mine.

1357
00:58:09,116 --> 00:58:10,384
That's wild.

1358
00:58:11,251 --> 00:58:13,687
Yes, that's Min Cheol's.
It looks good on you.

1359
00:58:14,121 --> 00:58:15,956
You didn't have to do this.

1360
00:58:15,956 --> 00:58:18,892
I wanted to talk,
but I didn't get the chance.

1361
00:58:18,892 --> 00:58:20,728
Right, that's true.

1362
00:58:21,695 --> 00:58:24,298
I think this is the first time
I've seen your face this close.

1363
00:58:24,298 --> 00:58:25,966
- Let's sit first.
- Yeah, sit down first.

1364
00:58:27,301 --> 00:58:28,268
What did you buy?

1365
00:58:28,268 --> 00:58:29,336
What is it?

1366
00:58:29,336 --> 00:58:31,071
This is from the café downstairs.

1367
00:58:31,572 --> 00:58:32,640
(Gasp)

1368
00:58:32,640 --> 00:58:34,475
What do we do? Do we share it?

1369
00:58:34,475 --> 00:58:35,943
She brought exactly what you like.

1370
00:58:35,943 --> 00:58:36,777
Right.

1371
00:58:36,777 --> 00:58:38,178
So the question is, can we share this?

1372
00:58:38,178 --> 00:58:40,681
She came to really lock it in.

1373
00:58:41,215 --> 00:58:44,018
She's never really talked
to Min Cheol's mother before.

1374
00:58:44,018 --> 00:58:45,486
To score points with her.

1375
00:58:46,287 --> 00:58:48,188
But what I appreciated was this.

1376
00:58:49,590 --> 00:58:52,526
When I first saw everyone,

1377
00:58:53,160 --> 00:58:55,496
I thought Min Cheol would be the oldest.

1378
00:58:55,496 --> 00:58:58,766
And the women all seemed young to me.

1379
00:58:58,766 --> 00:59:01,168
Everyone's pretty,
and it's hard to guess ages.

1380
00:59:01,168 --> 00:59:04,938
So I thought, "I should probably
let go of my expectations."

1381
00:59:05,372 --> 00:59:08,375
But even on the first night, I chose him.

1382
00:59:08,375 --> 00:59:09,710
- Really?
- Yes.

1383
00:59:10,344 --> 00:59:12,513
Can we say that
just among the three of us?

1384
00:59:12,513 --> 00:59:13,347
I don't know.

1385
00:59:14,615 --> 00:59:15,849
(While Jin Joo
and Min Cheol share a secret)

1386
00:59:15,849 --> 00:59:18,018
But shouldn't the person involved
be allowed to say it?

1387
00:59:18,919 --> 00:59:20,988
Let's go for a walk. I'm really full.

1388
00:59:20,988 --> 00:59:21,855
Okay.

1389
00:59:23,290 --> 00:59:24,625
(Seung Hak and Myo Jin go out for a walk.)

1390
00:59:24,625 --> 00:59:26,193
Should we take a longer walk tonight?

1391
00:59:26,193 --> 00:59:27,261
A longer one? Okay.

1392
00:59:27,261 --> 00:59:28,629
- To help digest.
- Sure.

1393
00:59:31,031 --> 00:59:32,166
So now,

1394
00:59:33,600 --> 00:59:34,668
have you decided on anything?

1395
00:59:37,338 --> 00:59:39,006
Or are you still torn?

1396
00:59:39,006 --> 00:59:41,275
Am I being too mean?

1397
00:59:41,809 --> 00:59:43,577
No, not at all.

1398
00:59:43,577 --> 00:59:47,414
I'm just torn.

1399
00:59:47,414 --> 00:59:50,050
I'm really torn. This is so hard.

1400
00:59:50,050 --> 00:59:53,487
I can't really enjoy this situation.

1401
00:59:53,487 --> 00:59:56,090
I've never been
in something like this before.

1402
00:59:58,025 --> 01:00:00,728
Then do you lean toward...

1403
01:00:00,728 --> 01:00:03,764
comfort, or more toward...

1404
01:00:03,764 --> 01:00:06,600
If I think about marriage,

1405
01:00:06,600 --> 01:00:09,236
I think I'd go for comfort.

1406
01:00:09,236 --> 01:00:12,272
But when I'm dating,
I think I seek excitement.

1407
01:00:12,272 --> 01:00:15,275
That makes sense.

1408
01:00:15,275 --> 01:00:16,276
Right.

1409
01:00:16,276 --> 01:00:19,680
But right now,

1410
01:00:19,680 --> 01:00:21,415
what do you seek?

1411
01:00:21,415 --> 01:00:24,485
Honestly,

1412
01:00:24,485 --> 01:00:27,988
what stirs my curiosity more is...

1413
01:00:27,988 --> 01:00:29,356
Yeah, I know what you mean.

1414
01:00:29,356 --> 01:00:32,760
Se Hoon does have more of that pull.

1415
01:00:32,760 --> 01:00:37,765
But when I'm with you,
I keep finding myself smiling.

1416
01:00:37,765 --> 01:00:40,467
Just seeing you makes me smile.

1417
01:00:40,467 --> 01:00:44,605
Normally, when I'm with Se Hoon,

1418
01:00:44,605 --> 01:00:48,242
it's more stimulating,

1419
01:00:48,242 --> 01:00:51,445
so you didn't really cross my mind.

1420
01:00:51,445 --> 01:00:54,081
But lately, when I'm with him,

1421
01:00:54,081 --> 01:00:56,950
your face suddenly pops into my head.

1422
01:00:56,950 --> 01:00:58,085
I was like, "Why?"

1423
01:00:58,085 --> 01:00:59,653
Am I kind of like smiling like this?

1424
01:01:00,487 --> 01:01:02,089
Behind Se Hoon?

1425
01:01:02,089 --> 01:01:03,290
"Look at me."

1426
01:01:03,290 --> 01:01:06,794
So between the two of you,

1427
01:01:06,794 --> 01:01:10,097
without meaning to...

1428
01:01:11,298 --> 01:01:14,969
Seung Hak kept expressing
his feelings so steadily...

1429
01:01:14,969 --> 01:01:17,871
and so consistently.

1430
01:01:18,505 --> 01:01:22,042
But Se Hoon is more like,

1431
01:01:22,042 --> 01:01:24,078
"I'm interested in two people."

1432
01:01:25,446 --> 01:01:27,348
And I'm similar, but still,

1433
01:01:29,016 --> 01:01:32,152
he's weighing two people too.

1434
01:01:33,020 --> 01:01:35,089
Taking all that into account,

1435
01:01:36,490 --> 01:01:38,292
I think someone
who keeps showing their feelings...

1436
01:01:38,292 --> 01:01:42,329
like Seung Hak might be better.

1437
01:01:42,329 --> 01:01:47,301
That thought just suddenly hit me.

1438
01:01:49,236 --> 01:01:52,973
Maybe that really is right.

1439
01:01:54,575 --> 01:01:57,244
Right now, the person I'm most drawn to
is Seung Hak.

1440
01:01:57,244 --> 01:02:00,280
And second is Se Hoon.

1441
01:02:01,682 --> 01:02:02,950
I had so much fun today.

1442
01:02:02,950 --> 01:02:03,917
Today?

1443
01:02:03,917 --> 01:02:07,655
It felt a bit different today too.

1444
01:02:07,655 --> 01:02:08,722
Right?

1445
01:02:09,723 --> 01:02:11,692
I really like your mother.

1446
01:02:11,692 --> 01:02:12,660
- Really?
- Yeah.

1447
01:02:13,193 --> 01:02:16,130
I was wondering
if my mother was enjoying this.

1448
01:02:16,130 --> 01:02:17,631
She looked like she was having fun.

1449
01:02:17,631 --> 01:02:18,499
Really?

1450
01:02:19,566 --> 01:02:22,903
I keep wondering if I've made things
harder for her because of me.

1451
01:02:22,903 --> 01:02:24,438
Like what?

1452
01:02:24,438 --> 01:02:25,873
What do you think?

1453
01:02:26,606 --> 01:02:29,509
I know this situation...

1454
01:02:30,810 --> 01:02:33,846
doesn't perfectly line up with
the kind of spouse she imagines for me.

1455
01:02:33,846 --> 01:02:35,815
So the choices I'm making right now...

1456
01:02:40,453 --> 01:02:42,088
But look.

1457
01:02:42,855 --> 01:02:49,696
The fact that you and I connected here...

1458
01:02:49,696 --> 01:02:52,365
came from a genuine place,

1459
01:02:53,266 --> 01:02:54,267
but does that mean...

1460
01:02:54,267 --> 01:02:56,169
it has to carry
such an overwhelming weight?

1461
01:02:56,703 --> 01:02:59,372
I really hope you don't see it that way.

1462
01:02:59,839 --> 01:03:03,209
I see it as a choice
that can always be revisited.

1463
01:03:03,209 --> 01:03:06,379
But that doesn't feel light.

1464
01:03:06,379 --> 01:03:07,847
Whatever choice I make.

1465
01:03:12,752 --> 01:03:13,786
The situation...

1466
01:03:15,855 --> 01:03:16,923
If she were,

1467
01:03:18,224 --> 01:03:22,195
say, born in 1998,

1468
01:03:24,330 --> 01:03:27,700
I'd go for her without any concerns.

1469
01:03:29,869 --> 01:03:33,439
But if things were to go wrong
halfway while trying to adjust,

1470
01:03:34,907 --> 01:03:39,045
then my time and her time
wouldn't feel the same.

1471
01:03:39,812 --> 01:03:41,447
To them, that time could feel much more...

1472
01:03:41,447 --> 01:03:43,750
like it was wasted.

1473
01:03:43,750 --> 01:03:44,918
Even if I don't see it as a waste.

1474
01:03:47,553 --> 01:03:51,891
This is really hard, honestly.

1475
01:03:56,329 --> 01:03:58,765
It's just...

1476
01:04:00,233 --> 01:04:01,100
really...

1477
01:04:02,135 --> 01:04:05,071
I'll think about it more.

1478
01:04:06,773 --> 01:04:10,777
(The final night comes to an end
amid deep concerns.)

1479
01:04:20,587 --> 01:04:22,055
At last, the decision day.

1480
01:04:22,055 --> 01:04:24,190
The day of the final decision has arrived.

1481
01:04:24,190 --> 01:04:26,159
- Decision Day.
- Yes.

1482
01:04:26,159 --> 01:04:28,528
(The long-awaited day
of the final decision)

1483
01:04:28,761 --> 01:04:32,198
(Early morning,
Han Gyeol and his mother get ready.)

1484
01:04:33,266 --> 01:04:37,370
(Han Gyeol is writing something.)

1485
01:04:38,004 --> 01:04:39,739
That's too long, Han Gyeol.

1486
01:04:41,608 --> 01:04:42,675
Mom.

1487
01:04:44,777 --> 01:04:47,113
I'll take care of this myself.

1488
01:04:48,548 --> 01:04:51,417
Putting your feelings
into words like that...

1489
01:04:53,820 --> 01:04:55,088
Looks like he's writing a letter.

1490
01:05:09,836 --> 01:05:10,803
Is she crying?

1491
01:05:12,171 --> 01:05:13,506
This doesn't feel good.

1492
01:05:19,112 --> 01:05:23,216
(Han Gyeol breaks down in tears
while writing the letter.)

1493
01:05:27,320 --> 01:05:28,721
Why? While writing the letter...

1494
01:05:29,722 --> 01:05:33,526
Is it something like, "I just can't
overcome the age difference"?

1495
01:05:34,327 --> 01:05:37,363
He must've burst into tears while writing.

1496
01:05:40,099 --> 01:05:41,167
Mom.

1497
01:05:42,235 --> 01:05:44,904
My goodness.

1498
01:05:45,538 --> 01:05:47,440
I feel so bad.

1499
01:05:48,675 --> 01:05:49,943
You feel bad?

1500
01:05:51,744 --> 01:05:52,645
Yeah.

1501
01:05:57,617 --> 01:05:58,985
Did you write your final letter?

1502
01:06:03,957 --> 01:06:07,160
The fact that he's crying means...

1503
01:06:09,228 --> 01:06:11,164
something he couldn't overcome.

1504
01:06:11,164 --> 01:06:13,333
It doesn't seem like a good sign.

1505
01:06:13,833 --> 01:06:16,302
In Match to Marry: With Parents,

1506
01:06:16,302 --> 01:06:20,540
we are looking for people who want to find
a partner together with their mother.

1507
01:06:20,540 --> 01:06:22,075
If you're interested in joining,

1508
01:06:22,075 --> 01:06:26,879
please don't hesitate to apply below.

1509
01:06:26,879 --> 01:06:30,016
We look forward to your applications.

1510
01:06:30,550 --> 01:06:32,385
For a couple to become a final match,

1511
01:06:32,385 --> 01:06:34,787
both mothers must approve...

1512
01:06:34,787 --> 01:06:36,723
their son's and daughter's choice.

1513
01:06:37,257 --> 01:06:38,591
(Everyone is in shock
at the final selection rule.)

1514
01:06:38,591 --> 01:06:39,792
This is insane.

1515
01:06:40,059 --> 01:06:43,630
(The mothers' final interviews
before the final decision)

1516
01:06:43,863 --> 01:06:45,298
What I'm stuck on now...

1517
01:06:45,298 --> 01:06:46,766
is not only the age difference.

1518
01:06:46,766 --> 01:06:48,534
Life really...

1519
01:06:48,534 --> 01:06:50,503
can't be filled with only good things.

1520
01:06:50,503 --> 01:06:51,971
Did she call them to persuade them?

1521
01:06:52,405 --> 01:06:53,706
Or to tell them to give up?

1522
01:06:53,706 --> 01:06:55,675
Then you just shouldn't make a choice.

1523
01:06:55,908 --> 01:06:56,976
You think so too, right?

1524
01:06:56,976 --> 01:06:57,944
Yes.

1525
01:06:57,944 --> 01:06:59,279
I don't think they'll make a choice.

1526
01:06:59,612 --> 01:07:02,448
We will now begin the final selection.

1527
01:07:02,448 --> 01:07:06,986
I will go to the person
who made my heart flutter.

1528
01:07:06,986 --> 01:07:07,887
I choose...

1529
01:07:07,887 --> 01:07:08,788
(Who will Han Gyeol choose?)

1530
01:07:08,788 --> 01:07:09,656
No way.

1531
01:07:11,958 --> 01:07:13,459
(The final gate, the mother's decision
Approval or rejection)

1532
01:07:13,459 --> 01:07:14,494
Is she still hesitating?

1533
01:07:14,861 --> 01:07:16,062
- My goodness.
- My goodness.

1534
01:07:16,996 --> 01:07:18,531
Really? Why?

1535
01:07:18,532 --> 01:07:19,432
Dramaday.me
